<p><b><img src="images/icons/icon11.gif" alt="Red face" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p><b>Chapter 7.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Onward through da icky swamp da three heroes charged.  For hours and hours, dey marched never stopping.  Well, ok, dey did stop once at a McNuglug's for a Big Nug and some fries, but dat's it.<br>
<br>
Through slime and stagnant water, dey trode.  Avoiding such dangers as mad frogloks, mean alligators, and female trolls in heat, our party finally made it to da trail dat lead out of da swamp.<br>
<br>
"Is this it?" an exhausted, slime-covered Lilting asked.<br>
<br>
"Me tink so," said Bash.  "Me pretty sure dis is da way to Halas."<br>
<br>
"This, my friends, is the way to Southern part of the Desert of Ro."  said Treehugger.  "Not exactly the fastest way to Halas, but probably the least dangerous.  I came through here from the town of Freeport.  We'll need to go there and head west.  From there, we'll need directions because that part of the land is new to me."<br>
<br>
"Ok den.  Dat sound good."<br>
<br>
Wit dat, da party walked da trail to Southern Ro.  Expecting desert, Bash and Lilting were surprised to see a lush, green landscape full of trees and grass as far as dey could see.<br>
<br>
"Why you lying son of a...!" da halfling started to say but was cut short.<br>
<br>
"Lilting!  Be nice.  Treehugger, dis not look like a desert."<br>
<br>
"I'm aware of that.  The desert is a few miles north of here.  There seems to be some magical barrier that prevents the desert from touching the swamp but I'm not sure if..." <br>
<br>
Da ranger was cut short when an orc approached dem.<br>
<br>
"Hul-lo," the orc said in a deep, raspy voice.  "Me are Smeg.  Smeg wants sell you copper coin for two silver!  Smeg say it good deal!"<br>
<br>
Bash fought da urge to pound the hated orc into vanilla pudding.  He never liked orcs and never trusted dem.  Lilting spoke for dem all.<br>
<br>
"Well, that sounds like an 'ok' deal Smeg, but I think we're not interested."<br>
<br>
Just den, Bash felt his hammer become warm.  It became warmer and warmer and he didn't know why.<br>
<br>
"Right," said Treehugger, "We've no time for orc deals."<br>
<br>
Just den, Smeg smiled and four orcs appeared out of da trees and surrounded da little party.  Bash's hammer flared up.  It turned bright white and was berry hot to da touch.  For some reason, Bash not minded it and no dropped it.<br>
<br>
"Smeg think that since you no like deal, he say you die!" the orc said.  Da four orcs all wit weapons drawn, closed in on da group of good guys.<br>
<br>
Treehuggers swords instantly appeared.  Lilting pulled out a tiny, tiny, miniscule dagger.<br>
<br>
Da orcs rushed in.  Treehugger took da orc nearest to him.  Lilting squealed like a little girl as one orc rushed him.  Bash felt da heat from da hammer and almost seemed to speak to him.  It wanted orc blood.<br>
<br>
Treehugger had little trouble fighting his orc.  Da orc was clumsy and stupid.  Treehugger was not.  Slapping da silly orc's club dis way and dat and kicking it square in da chest, da orc just got madder as it fell backwards to da ground.  It sprung back up with a mean sneer on its face.  Treehugger grinned.<br>
<br>
Lilting, on da udder hand, was scared out of his little britches.  He saw big, nasty, green orc charging at him with a shortsword.  His first instinct was to run.  But some, sane, rational, quiet part of his mind told him not to.  He instead, on instinct alone, started to use da same trick he tried on da bixie.  He started to cast da Spirit of da Wolf on da orc.<br>
<br>
Bash was oblivious to everyting but one orc charging in on him.  Da orc let out a little snarl.  Bash let out a roar.  A deafening roar.  A roar dat would have made a giant lion proud.  A warrior's roar.  Dis made da orc slow down a little bit in confusion.  It was all da time Bash needed to bring up his hammer and send it swinging down towards da orc's head at a blinding speed.<br>
<br>
Treehugger seemed to be having a little bit too much fun taunting and mocking his orc opponent.  Da orc would swing his club at da ranger only to find dat da ranger would swing his swords underneath the club and force it back at da orc.  Da club would den smack da orc's face.  <br>
<br>
Da half-elf realized da trouble Lilting might be in and decided to end his own fun.  He turned his back to da orc and with a quick backwards thrust slammed his longsword into da orc's gut.  And without even turning around, Treehugger quickly bent backwards and  thrust his shortsword in an upward motion dat arced right into da orc's head.  Treehugger quickly bent forward again to stand upright and da orc just fell limply to da ground.<br>
<br>
Lilting quickly began da words to his spell.  "Spirit of Wolf I beg of you; enter this orc, oh please do!"  And wit dat, da orc started to run at twice da speed it did before.  Da halfling pointed his dagger straight at da orc and shut his eyes in a wincing manner.<br>
<br>
Da orc, fully surprised dat it was moving much more quickly now, realized much too late what to do about it.  Before it had a chance for its brain to tell its feet to stop moving, da orc looked down and saw dat it's chest was bloody.<br>
<br>
Lilting opened his eyes to see a very shocked orc impaled on his tiny, tiny, oh-so tiny dagger.  Da orc looked at its chest wound, looked up at Lilting, and looked down again.  It den finally fell backwards, dead as a doornail.<br>
<br>
Bash's hammer came straight towards da orc.  Da orc, realizing it's doom, swung its sword at da ogre in desperation in da hopes it would hit someting.  A split second latter, where an orc once was, dere was just a messy mess of orc splat.<br>
<br>
"Did you see that?!" and excited Lilting exclaimed loudly as he ran up to Bash.  "It worked!  My theory worked!  Woo hoo!"<br>
<br>
Just den, da fourth orc charged at Lilting (me said four orcs surrounded dem, remember?).  Not even noticing, Lilting just danced around.  Without even tinking, Bash dropped his hammer, picked up Lilting, straightened da halfling's little arm dat was holding da dagger, and threw da little guy at da orc like a spear.<br>
<br>
Screaming through the air (not just a figure of speech, Lilting literally was screaming), Lilting headed right for da orc.  Da orc stopped and just watched dis blurry little guy come right at him.  Da orc exploded as da halfling went right through it like a warm knife in butter.<br>
<br>
Bash picked up his hammer and stomped over to an onlooking Smeg.  Treehugger jogged up right next to him.  Both had weapons drawn ready to finish off da devious orc.<br>
<br>
"Smeg sees you are not stupid customers." da orc said nervously.  "Smeg make deal.  Smeg sell copper piece for one silver instead of two."<br>
<br>
Bash looked at Treehugger, and da ranger silently nodded at da ogre.<br>
<br>
"Ok den," said Bash.  "Dat is a good deal.  Here is yous money."  And wit dat, dey purchased da copper coin and Smeg walked away.<br>
<br>
"Wow.  I can't believe I survived that!  I thought I was surely done for.  That orc came real close to killing me!" da ranger said with no amount of sarcasm.  "If you guys hadn't been there I....  say, Bash, you're wounded!"<br>
<br>
Bash looked down.  His thigh was sliced open by da first orc he smashed.  He didn't even realize it before, but now dat he did, it burned like fire.  Da blood was coming out pretty rapidly.<br>
<br>
"What we need is a cleric," Treehugger said.  "A cleric could heal that, no problem.  Plus, a cleric <b>might</b> be able to keep me alive longer than 24 hours.  Maybe I'd be able to live 48.  I doubt it though."<br>
<br>
"Ok den," Bash said as he grinned against da pain.  "Where can us find one of dem?"<br>
<br>
"Oasis, I bet.  They're always hanging around there to heal up the idiots who think they can take on crocodiles."<br>
<br>
"Ok den.  Let's go dere."<br>
<br>
Just then, Lilting slowly wobbled up with arms outstretched and a look of shock on his face.  Da halfling looked down and noticed he was completely covered in orc goo.<br>
<br>
"EWWWWWWWWWW!!!!!" da halfling screamed.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
