<p><b>Chapter 11.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
"Ha ha!" da knight shouted.  "Your evil taint will foul this magnificent city no more, dragon!  Taste holy steel!"<br>
<br>
Da townspeople of Freeport knew dat cry well.  It was da ravings of da local village idiot, Sir Yessir.  Some said Yessir used to be a great paladin, but too many blows to da head ended him up here.  Some said he never was a paladin because no holy order would let such a fool in deir ranks.  Some just didn't give a rats foot what his past was.<br>
<br>
In da middle of one of da crowded streets of Freeport, a tiny lizard scuttled by.  Hearing da battlecry of Yessir moments before, da villagers in da street were smart enough to split apart and make room for the soon-to-follow bumbling idiot.  Sure enough, da knight came around da corner at a full run.  Losing sight of his prey, he came to a halt.<br>
<br>
Sir Yessir was dressed in a patchwork of rusted armor full of chinks, holes, and dents.  A tarnished sword and a trash can lid served as his weaponry.  An old bucket dat was used for wellwater was atop his head used as a helmet.  Bits of da man's grey hair jutted out from underneath da helmet in a random, chaotic pattern.  Blue eyes wide open searching, his weatherworn face tightened wit concentration.<br>
<br>
A little girl giggled at da funny man.  Yessier noticed da little girl and hobbled over to her, armor squeaking all da way.  He bent down to see da girl face to face.<br>
<br>
"My lady, didst thou see where the fearsome dragon went?" said Yessir to da small girl.<br>
<br>
Da girl giggled and nodded.  She den pointed down da street in da direction da lizard ran.<br>
<br>
"A thousand thank yous, my lovely lady.  Be not afraid, for I am Yessir the Dragon's Bane!"  Yessir kissed da girl's hand while she giggled some more.  He den stood up and bowed, and den ran off in da direction da girl had indicated.<br>
<br>
Da girl's mother scolded da little girl for talking to da knight and da crowd of people went back to deir daily business.<br>
<br>
"Ah ha!  There you are!  You could not hide from me forever, dragon!" Yessir had found da  dragon in da courtyard outside of a tavern.  "You shall not elude me with your tricks again!"<br>
<br>
Da lizard just perched itself on a branch oblivious to anyting around it udder dan da bug it was gonna eat.<br>
<br>
"Prepare to burn in Hate!" da knight shouted.  Yessir smacked his sword against his make-shift shield and charged.<br>
<br>
Da lizard stuck its tongue out and caught a bug.  It began munching happily until da sword came down and split it into two pieces.<br>
<br>
"Triumph!  Triumph for the Holy Order!  One less dragon to spread its evil across this land!"  da paladin said wit his sword raised high into da air.  He den kneeled down and stuck his sword into da ground.  Yessir den gave tanks to his god for imbuing him wit da power to be da greatest dragonslayer dat ever  walked Norrath.<br>
<br>
Finishing his prayer, da knight stood up and looked around.  Noticing da convenient tavern nearby, da knight became thirsty.  "I think my victory deserves a toast!"<br>
<br>
And wit dat, da paladin took off his helmet and walked into da bar.<br>
