<p><b><img src="images/icons/Laugh_Blue.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p><b>Chapter 13.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Bash stood on da street corner tapping his big foot impatiently.  He told his group to meet back here in one hour.  Dat hour had been up over half an hour ago.  <br>
<br>
Bash was getting more angry by da minute, and had just about almost resolved to go continue da journey on his own when he saw two silhouettes approaching from down one of da streets.<br>
<br>
"Shut up!" said one of da peoples.<br>
<br>
"No, you shut up!" said da udder.<br>
<br>
"No you!"<br>
<br>
Bash saw dat da two peoples coming were Medsa and and a sludge-covered Treehugger.  Dey both not looked berry happy.<br>
<br>
"Hey, why is yous fighting?" asked Bash.<br>
<br>
With a frustrated scream, Medsa just said "Why don't you ask hormone boy here?!"<br>
<br>
"Me?!  I didn't jump into that food trough  voluntarily!  Some pyscho witch who doesn't know a good man when she sees one pushed me!"<br>
<br>
"Well, if you hadn't followed me everywhere I went and actually split up like Bash  said, maybe you would  be high and dry right now!"<br>
<br>
Bash, trying to follow da converation, said, "Me take it yous not find someone to help us?"<br>
<br>
Medsa and Treehugger both instantly turned to da ogre and simultaneously yelled, "NO!!"<br>
<br>
"Ah.  Ok den.  Me neither.  Peoples here no like ogres much, so me couldn't get much more dan a scream from most."<br>
<br>
"And another thing," began Medsa to da ranger, "This whole, 'I'm gonna die tomorrow for sure, so how about some lovin' routine is getting really old!"<br>
<br>
"Well, it's true!  Pretty soon my luck is going to run out and I'll be killed! I suck at fighting!"<br>
<br>
"You suck at a lot of things!"<br>
<br>
Bash just rolled his eyes and threw his big ogre hands up in da air and turned around and let da two crazy peoples go at it.  Dat's when he saw da halfling.<br>
<br>
Lilting trotting along wit a big smile on his face came bounding towards da ogre.  Behind him, an old man hurriedly walked behind da halfling with armor creaking and  squeaking noisily.<br>
<br>
"Hi guys!" said da halfling even more excited dan normal.  "Guess what I found!"<br>
<br>
"A whino?" Treehugger guessed.<br>
<br>
"Nope!  A great knight who's willing to join our cause against evil!"<br>
<br>
Da old man attempted to make an elaborate bow, but his armor and old legs somewhat prevented dat.<br>
<br>
"He's the greatest dragonslayer that ever lived!  He's killed more than forty dragons in his day!"  Lilting barely could contain his excitement at his find.  Bash would surely be proud, he was certain!  Turning to da old man, da halfling said "Go ahead!  Tell them about the Dragon of Qeynos and how you tricked it into drowning!"<br>
<br>
"Yes, of course!" da old man said.  "There I was, polishing my armor, when I hear this tremendous roar..."<br>
<br>
Bash couldn't quite put his big ogre finger on it, but dis man seemed a little odd to him.  Medsa and Treehugger just cocked one eyebrow at each other not knowing what to tink of da knight.<br>
<br>
"Save yous story, old man." Bash said.  "Us is sure you're a good hero, but..."<br>
<br>
"But what?" asked Lilting a little sad about what he might hear next.<br>
<br>
"...but, us not sure about yous skills.  Us really is needing a guide to Halas right now more dan a 'dragonslayer'."<br>
<br>
"My boy," said da knight, "Not only do I know the way to that frigid region, but I personally have slain 12 ice dragons there!  I can show you the way, with most certainty!"<br>
<br>
Bash considered his words.  Dey needed to get to Halas as quick as possible, and dis crazy old man seemed to know da way.  Da ogre shrugged.<br>
<br>
"Ok den.  Yous can come."<br>
<br>
"Thank ye, my good fellow.  Ye'll not regret it!  I, am Sir Yessir!  Evil trembles before me!"<br>
<br>
And wit dat, da party headed westward out of Freeport wit Yessir telling of his good deeds, Lilting listening intently, Bash tromping ahead focusing on his goal, and Medsa and Treehugger bickering some more.<br>
<br>
