<p><b><img src="images/icons/Dizzy_Face.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p><b>Chapter 14.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
In da huge forest of Faydark, nestled snugly deep within, was da tree city of Kelethin.  Dis was da home of da tiny, wussier elves of da lands lovingly referred to as wood elves.  Long ago, it was decreed dat calling dese elves "Tiny Wussy Elves" didn't go over well wit da Kelethin residents, so da races just created da term "wood elves" as an accepted standard.<br>
<br>
Dese wood elves were a clumsy sort.  Dey was always falling flat on deir faces.  Some said dat da race was magically born wit da subconscious desire to kiss dirt, udders just  believed dey had no coordination.  In any case, da ancient wood elves long ago decided to erect a city dat was as far from da ground as possible.  Da theory was, "If us is not near da ground, den us can't smack it wit our faces!"  Like most theories, when it was applied to da real world it didn't work berry well.<br>
<br>
"Hail, NoodleArm!" said a wood elf as he walked into one of da Kelethin shops.  Da wood elf took a few more steps and den fell flat on his face.<br>
<br>
"Hail, Jammypants!" said da dark brown haired elf.  "Need some more supplies?"<br>
<br>
Getting off da floor and rubbing his nose, Jammypants just got up and smiled.  Dis was a regular occurrance for a wood elf. <br>
<br>
Turning to look out his shop window at da beautiful day, NoodleArm noticed a couple wood elves walking along one of da ramps high in da trees.  Like clockwork, dey both began to stumble and den fall right off completely.  A short scream was heard by dem and den dey fell out of da shopkeepers sight.<br>
<br>
"What have you got for sale today?" asked Jammypants.<br>
<br>
"Same stuff as yesterday," said NoodleArm.  Three more screams erupted from wood elves outside as dey lost deir footing and tumbled seventy feet to da ground.<br>
<br>
"Heard anything about the trouble brewing?"<br>
<br>
"What trouble?"<br>
<br>
"I was just making small talk.  There's no trouble.  Especially not here in this wonderful city."  Jammypants fell on his face again and two more wood elves outside could be heard falling to deir doom.<br>
<br>
Just den, da shopkeeper heard a different sound amidst da sound of wood elves hitting dirt.  It sounded like da flapping of two huge, slow bird wings.  Jammypants and NoodleArm looked around da shop in confusion.<br>
<br>
<i>Whoosh.   Whoosh.   Whoosh.</i><br>
<br>
Jammypants stood up and shrugged at da shopkeeper.  Da beating of da huge wing-like tings stopped and da whole city shook like someting monstrous had jumped up and down on one of da platforms.  <br>
<br>
A nasty, loud, deep, bloodcurdling roar was den heard.  Jammypants and NoodleArm became berry afraid.  Dey didn't know what was going on.  Screams of terror erupted from many wood elves outside.  Da two elves in da shop heard many elves running around in a panic, and even more falling off da city and to da ground.  Some even on purpose.<br>
<br>
"<b>Come back here and face me</b>!" a deep, booming, gutteral voice yelled.  "<b>You will answer my question or be destroyed</b>!"<br>
<br>
Jammypants quivered in fear and so did da shopkeeper.  More screams from da elves outside did nothing to calm deir nerves.  All of a sudden, dey could hear da ting outside move closer to da shop.<br>
<br>
Da whole shop shook more violently wit each booming step.  Da footsteps came to a halt where it seemed to be just outside da door to da shop.<br>
<br>
Dere was complete silence and da two elves just stared at da door.  Too scared to move.  Too scared to fall down.  Too scared to wee wee.<br>
<br>
A gigantic, black-clawed, red hand smashed through da door and swung upward to rip off da ceiling of da shop.  A fifteen foot tall demon stood snarling over da elves.<br>
<br>
Jammypants let out a shriek and started to run, but da demon snatched him up and bit him in half wit his massive jaws.  NoodleArm just  stared in utter horror.  Den da demon moved over to him.<br>
<br>
Da demon picked up da shopkeeper and brought da elves face just inches from its own.  NoodleArm could barely breathe da fetid breath coming from da demon's mouth.  Blank white eyes stared back at him wit pure hatred.<br>
<br>
"<b>What do you know of a heroic party heading towards Halas, elf boy</b>!?" da demon asked in an otherworldly voice.  NoodleArm just shivered wit fear.  "<b>Answer me</b>!!"<br>
<br>
NoodleArm just froze up in shock.  Da demon, realizing he was not going to get any information from dese clumsy, wussy elves decided to try to acquire it elsewhere.<br>
<br>
"Maybe that idiot Crush will know something," da demon mumbled.<br>
<br>
Da demon took to da sky once again and headed north.  Da last thing heard was da scream of NoodleArm as he was flung into da mist below Kelethin.<br>
<br>
