<p><b><img src="images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Post" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p><b>Chapter 16.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Traveling for two days straight, our heroic party had trudged through da commonlands.  Yessir was now in da lead as everyone else was too exhausted to even move.  But, wit da warnings of da paladin saying dey no could stop until dey reached East Karana, da party received no rest.<br>
<br>
"Ah! Here we are," said da knight.  Da party reached da entrance to da haunted Kithicor Forest.<br>
<br>
Lilting gave a frown.  He knew of dis forest, but he no had explored it much.  He heard too many ghost stories to even tink about going in.<br>
<br>
"Isn't this place haunted?" da halfling asked as he saw da moon beginning to rise as da night slowly began around dem.<br>
<br>
"Of course it is!" sad Sir Yessir.  Everyone in da party got a look of terror on deir faces.  "But fear not!  For 'tis only haunted by day!  Never at night!"<br>
<br>
Everyone heaved a sigh of relief.  Everyone except Medsa, who had to keep shoving Treehugger away.  "Get away from me!  I don't need any of your comfort to get rid of my fear!" said da cleric.<br>
<br>
"But I do!" da ranger said with shivers.<br>
<br>
Da cleric just sneered at Treehugger.<br>
<br>
"Ok, lads!" said Yessir.  "Let's hurry up and get through this place as quickly as possible before the morning dawns!"<br>
<br>
Da group trotted along following da crazy paladin.  Dey ran into da forest and it looked pretty spooky.  Each tree seemed like it was dying and dey felt like dey was being watched from every angle.<br>
<br>
Dey continued running along da path through da forest.  Spooky hoots and howls could be heard all around dem.  Lilting wanted to run away.  Bash wanted to smash da dumb owl hooting.  Treehugger wanted to be held because he was so afraid.  Medsa wanted da ranger to leave her alone.<br>
<br>
Dey was making good time for about half an hour when all of a sudden dey was ambushed by a group of skeletal mages and zombies.  Da undead tings jumped out of da trees and bushes and surrounded da party.<br>
<br>
"Ye know, come to think of it, I think I may have been mistaken" da paladin began saying outloud but tinking to himself.  "I think maybe the forest is haunted at night and not by day."<br>
<br>
Treehugger's swords instantly appeared in his hands.  Bash readied his hammer.  Medsa placed her hands on her hips and glared at da  undead tings.  Lilting drew out his tiny, tiny, almost microscopic dagger.  Yessir still contemplated if he truly was wrong about da forest being haunted in da daytime.<br>
<br>
"You'll not take us without a fight!" da ranger said wit a snarl.  "I'm sure I'm no match for you, but my friends will take you down after I die!"<br>
<br>
Just den, da biggest, meanest skeleton made its way through da circle of undead.  It carried a huge doubled bladed axe in one of its massive hands.  It looked at da little ranger dan den laughed.  It was at dat moment, Bash found he was frozen in place and  couldn't move.  Da udders noticed da same ting about demselves.<br>
<br>
Da zombies in da undead group all had hungry glints in deir eyes.  Da skeletons raised deir weapons.  Dey all started moving in closer.  Da big skeleton raised his gigantic axe, and den swung it downwards towards Bash's head.<br>
<br>
"Wait!  Wait!  Stop!" yelled a voice from somewhere behind Bash.  He no could see who it was, but da voice sounded familiar somehow.  "Stop!  Hold on!"<br>
<br>
Da big skeleton's axe stopped just inches away from Bash's forehead.  All da udder undead stopped deir advance as well.  Out of da corner of his eye, Bash saw da big skeleton look at da unseen figure and den walked in its direction.  He heard da person talking to da skeleton, but he could barely make it out.<br>
<br>
"Right," said da voice.  "I'm aware of the deal.  But these guys are not a part of it.  They're my friends!  And you know what happens if you hurt my frends."<br>
<br>
Bash knew he had heard dat voice before, but he could not figure out where.  Dis was worse  torture dan waiting for da skeletons and zombies to eat him.<br>
<br>
"Exactly.  Now, release my friends before I get mad!"<br>
<br>
All of a sudden, Bash found he could move once again.  He spun around to see who da voice belong to.  Dere, standing in front of da huge skeleton, was a tiny gnome wit a brown robe.<br>
<br>
"Phil!" shouted Bash wit relief.  "Me glad to see yous!"<br>
<br>
Phil looked at da big ogre and smiled.  Den he turned his attention back towards da big skeleton.  "So what do you have to say for yourself?"<br>
<br>
Da skeleton moved it's jaw like it was talking, but no words came out.  Only da sound of bone scraping against bone could be heard.<br>
<br>
"All right then," said Phil.  "But don't apologize to me.  Apologize to my friends!"<br>
<br>
Da skeleton opened and closed its mouth and shrugged its shoulders like it was sighing.  Den, it turned towards da group and moved its jaw again like it was saying someting.<br>
<br>
"That's better!  Now don't you feel better?"<br>
<br>
Da skeleton looked down and den moved its mouth slightly like it was muttering someting under its breath.<br>
<br>
"Ok, now make sure my friends get out of this forest safely, ok?  I would be upset to find out they didn't have your protection.  Most upset."<br>
<br>
Da big skeleton nodded.<br>
<br>
Done wit talking to da skeleton, Phil excitedly ran up to da party.  "Hi guys!  You still on your adventure?  Is it fun?"<br>
<br>
"Hiya Phil!" said Lilting.  "We're glad to see you."<br>
<br>
Treehugger and Medsa said sarcastically at da same time, "Yeah.  Real glad."  Realizing dat she was tinking along da same lines as himself, Treehugger winked at da cleric.  Medsa just rolled her eyes in disgust.<br>
<br>
Just den, anudder skeleton came running up da trail through da woods.  It was Jakontiklarkiak, da same skeleton dey saw wit  Phil in Oasis.  Jakontiklarkiak waved to Bash and den saw da udder skeletons dat were gonna eat da group.  It jumped up wit joy and ran over to dem.<br>
<br>
Jakontik jerked his head up quickly as if to say, "Wassup?" to da group of skeletons and zombies.  One of da skeletons held out its hand and Jakoktik slapped it wit his own.  He patted a zombie on da back and den began moving his jaw like da big skeleton did before.  Da udder skeletons did da same.  Da zombies just made moans and growl sounds.<br>
<br>
"Anyway," said Phil, "You've got clearance to pass through the forest now.  Skeleton kings can be so fickle when it comes to tresspassers.  Not to worry though.  He'll make sure you get through safe.  If he doesn't, he'll be sorry and he knows it."<br>
<br>
"Wow," said Bash, "Yous is pretty powerful to command da king."<br>
<br>
"Well, duh.  I'm a necromancer.  I have more power than a god!  I'm just waiting for Hate to freeze over so I can join you guys!  You're so cool!"<br>
<br>
Not wanting to be around da annoying necro much longer, Bash decided it was time to go.<br>
<br>
"Ok peoples, let's go.  Tanks for helping us Phil.  Us will give yous a shout when it ok for yous to join us."<br>
<br>
"Okie dokie!  I'll be waiting!"<br>
<br>
Da party den said deir goodbyes and began marching westward once more.  Yessir, not having said a word, had his brow furrowed in concentration da whole time.  He finally spoke up as he lead da way.<br>
<br>
"Ye know, I've been thinking about it.  I'm pretty sure the woods is haunted in the daytime.  I don't think I was wrong."<br>
<br>
Bash sighed and den looked at Lilting.  Da halfling seemed to be looking northward and was crying a little bit.  Da ogre decided not to bug da halfling.<br>
<br>
Dey reached da trail dat led out of da woods and evntually found deir way to East Karana.  Dey decided dis was a good place to rest.  It was a good idea, until Bash's clothes suddenly and magically burst into flame.<br>
<br>
[This message has been edited by Numbuk (edited 09-12-2000).]</p>
