<i>Posted by Numbuk on 09-14-2000 11:16 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/Disco_Ball_Face.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p><b>Chapter 17.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Bash smelled smoke and looked down to see his pants and shirt engulfed in flames.  Confused for only a second, panic took over as da heat found its way to his skin.<br>
<br>
"AAAAHHHH!!! PUT IT OUT!  PUT IT OUT!" da ogre screamed as he ran around in circles.<br>
<br>
Da group, not exactly sure what was happening, each had deir own ideas of which was da best ting for Bash to do in dis situation.<br>
<br>
"Keep running and the fire will get tired!" said Lilting.<br>
<br>
"Flap your arms faster to fan out the flames!" said Treehugger.<br>
<br>
"Stand still and act like something that doesn't look like it would burn!" said Yessir.<br>
<br>
Medsa just calmly said, "How about Bashing that woman over there with the flaming hands laughing at you?"<br>
<br>
The whole party turned to see who Medsa was talking about.  Everyone, except Bash of course.  He was still running around in a panic.  The woman dat da cleric had pointed out was a dark skinned, dark haired erudite wit a red robe.  Her eyes were orange, like dey demselves were ablaze.  She was cackling wildly at da sight of da flaming ogre.<br>
<br>
"Let's go take her out!" said Treehugger.  "You guys can use my corpse as a shield if she starts getting rough!"<br>
<br>
Medsa thought dat was a good idea.  Da group, minus Bash, walked over to da much-too-happy erudite.  Her cackling abruptly stopped and her eyes snapped to da peoples now standing in front of her.<br>
<br>
"Go away!" she said wit a hiss.  "This doesn't concern you!"<br>
<br>
"You set our friend on fire!" said Treehugger.  "Of course it concerns us!"<br>
<br>
A big ball of flame da size of an ogre ran by da party screaming loudly.  Nobody seemed to notice as all focus was on da erudite woman.<br>
<br>
"If that magical fire is tied to ye, m'lady, then I am guessin' it will be extinguished with your life!" da paladin said.<br>
<br>
"Sorry, no.  It's normal fire.  Now, if you'll excuse me, I've got more things to burn."<br>
<br>
Da erudite's hands started to glow red and flames danced about dem.  She shot out fire balls into trees and bushes and anyting else nearby.  She cackled some more as she watched da flames rise up.<br>
<br>
"Listen, you witch...!" started Lilting.<br>
<br>
"Wizard.  I'm a wizard, well, wizardess.  I'm not a witch!"<br>
<br>
"Listen, you wizardess!" Lilting corrected himself, "You help our friend right now!"<br>
<br>
"Why should I?  You know, I haven't seen a roasted halfling in a while..."<br>
<br>
Lilting immediately shut up.<br>
<br>
Medsa realized dey was getting nowhere.  Noticing dat dis lady had some decent fire summoning power, and her seemingly overjoyment of setting tings ablaze, she got an idea.  "Look, we're on a quest.  A quest that our large friend has undertaken.  We'd like it if you came along.  There will be many, many, many things that are combustable along the way."<br>
<br>
"Lots of things that will burn?" da woman asked as her eyes lit up.  "Really?"<br>
<br>
"Uh..... yes." said da cleric.  "Lots of things to burn.  Will you help us?"<br>
<br>
Da big ball of flame ran screaming by again.  Like before, no one noticed.<br>
<br>
"If you say there's things to burn, then count me in!" da wizardess said happily.  "My name is Pyra.  Pyra Maniaca."<br>
<br>
"I'm Medsa," said Medsa (obviously), "And this is Lilting, Yessir, and this cute...er... ugly guy is Treehugger."<br>
<br>
"And your large friend?"<br>
<br>
Everyone's mouth dropped as dey remembered deir big, burning friend.  Dey looked around for Bash.  Dey saw him running around in circles, stopping, and den spinning place.  Screaming still, but more out of panic and fear dan pain.<br>
<br>
"He's Bash!" said Lilting.  "He's the nicest ogre in the world!  Can you please put out the fire?"<br>
<br>
"No.  I can't."<br>
<br>
"What?!" said da halfling.  He turned to da cleric.  "You said she could help him!"<br>
<br>
Da cleric shrugged.  "I thought she might, since she set him on fire in the first place."<br>
<br>
"I can't put the fires out," said Pyra, "But that river can.  Maybe you guys should have told him to jump in it."<br>
<br>
Da group looked over to where da wizard was pointing.  Dey all smacked deir foreheads.  Dey all hurriedly ran towards da bright, burning ogre.<br>
<br>
"Bash!" said Lilting.  "Hurry!  Follow me to that river!  If you jump in, it'll put out the fire!"  Da halfling took off towards da river.<br>
<br>
Bash, still in a fearful panic, got up and ran after da halfling.  He saw dat Lilting stopped near da edge of da water.<br>
<br>
"Here!  Here!  Jump in!  Quick!"<br>
<br>
Witout hesitation, da big ogre jumped into da river.  He landed wit a humongous splash.  Steam hissed and rose from da water as da flames were extinguished.  Bash's eyes rolled back and he let out a berry, berry contented sigh.<br>
<br>
Da udders reached da edge of da water and saw da ogre bathing in extreme pleasure.  Bash, noticing he was being watched. quickly stood up.  Unfortunately, da ogre's clothes were burned to a black crisp and dey just broke apart into flakes and fell of his ogrish body.<br>
<br>
A good laugh was had by all, except for a very beet red Bash.<br>
<br>
Da naked ogre climbed out of da water.  Lilting noticed dat da ogre did not have a burn on him.  He thought it odd.  But not as odd as da hammer dat Bash had in his hand now looked.<br>
<br>
"Bash!  Look at your hammer!"<br>
<br>
Bash looked down at his hammer and saw dat it was pulsating berry, berry rapidly.  It was turning from white to orange with extreme speed.  Bash had no idea what was wrong wit it.  Figuring he could smack some sense back into his grandpa's mallet, he swung it towards a nearby boulder on da ground.<br>
<br>
Da hammer hit wit such force dat it created da sound of lightning striking nearby.  Da rock was instantly smashed into a thousand, burnt pieces.  A ring of fire exploded outward from da point of impact.  Bash was amazed at by what his hammer was doing, and by da fact dat da fire dat passed through him from da hammer did not harm himself in any way.<br>
<br>
Lilting was not so lucky.  Da blast wave hit da little guy wit such power dat it knocked him completely off his feet.  He landed into da river.<br>
<br>
Everyone just stood completely still wit jaws agape and eyes wide open, including Bash.  Da big ogre even forgot he was naked, let alone burn-free from da previous fire.<br>
<br>
Shaking da shock of da hammer-blast free, da party realized what happened to da halfling.  Dey all went rushing up to da river's edge.  <br>
All dey saw was da tiny outline of a halfling being pulled downstream, and den out of view.<br>
<br>
