<p><i>(me is writing dis immediately after 18... so be sure yous not missed last chapter)</i><br>
<br>
<b>Chapter 19.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Far away, on da very peak of da highest mountain top for as far as da eye could see, stood a pitch black castle.  Da walls of the castle glistened in da light as if dey was covered wit some type of dark slime.  Dis castle would have glistened brighter, but da sun was not out.  It was eternally hidden by deep, grey, overcast sky.  No pure light ever entered dis place it seemed.<br>
<br>
Inside da castle, Smellybreath, da goblin wizard, stood atop an altar made of arcane runes and symbols.  With arms outsrethed to ceiling, da goblin was chanting in some arcane tongue dat anyone within earshot would  not have known.<br>
<br>
Da only spectators da goblin had were four knights.  Dese knights wore armour as black as da castle walls.  Each held swords with blades equally as dark, but wit blood-red hilts.  None of da knights faces could be seen for each wore a full helmet wit sharp horns justting out of da sides.  Dey stood like silent statues as Smellybreath continued his chanting.<br>
<br>
"Ooom bop zoppa doo wop zoppa doo wah ditty," da goblin continued.  Da goblin's body began to glow blue and a humming sound could be heard hanging in da air. His chanting continued uninterrupted.<br>
<br>
"Oooh Eee Oooh Ahh Ahh ting tang walla walla bing bang..."  As da goblin continued speaking getting progressively louder and louder, his body began glowing even a brighter shade of blue.  Da humming also continued to get louder while da color kept getting lighter and lighter.  It became so light and so bright, dat da goblins body was engulfed in a pure white luminescence.<br>
<br>
Smellybreath was screaming his magical incantation to be heard over da loud and throbbing humming sound.  He couldn't see anything anymore.  He finally cried out da final words, "<b>Shayka bom bom, shayka bom bom</b>!!"  <br>
<br>
As da last words exited da goblins mouth, Smellybreath flung his outstretched arms towards da black knights.  All da light dat encompassed his body was shot out into four directions and slammed into each of da black warriors.  Each  knight jolted and and convulsed as da light seared through deir bodies.  None made a sound as da light arced and twisted around each knight.<br>
<br>
Within seconds, the light disappeared and all was dark within the goblin's hidden sanctum once again, save for the light of the torches on the walls.<br>
<br>
Da goblin collapsed on his altar from overexertion.  Rising to his elbows, da goblin managed to speak in rasped breaths.<br>
<br>
"There.... it is.... done!  You.... are now infused with the powers of the elements themselves...."<br>
<br>
Da knights, each looking down at deir swords, noticed dat each glowed very brightly.  Each, also, glowed wit a different color; blue, orange, white, and brown.<br>
<br>
"You are now the guardians.... of what will be ... the future Lord of the Planes.  You are now imbued with powers that are more ancient than time itself.  I now.... dub each of you.... with the names of your respective magics.<br>
<br>
"Fire.  Ice.  Earth.  Air.   Your are now the Elemental Guardians.  And I.... have just brought forth the second stage of.... the prophecy.<br>
<br>
"Go now.... guard each corner of the castle.... until I call upon you again."<br>
<br>
Each knight silently nodded and turned around and began hurriedly exiting da room.  Da goblin held up a tiny finger da largest of da knights.<br>
<br>
"Wait.... you.... you will be my personal guardian.  You will be the general of the other three.  Such a calling will grant you more power than what you have just received, so.... so states the prophecy.  Do not fail me."<br>
<br>
Da knight banged his guantleted fist against da chest of his black breastplate and turned around and marched to his post.<br>
<br>
