<p><b><img src="images/icons/Laugh_Blue.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p><b>Chapter 22.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Treehugger immediately recognized da annoying facial imprint in da mud.  He stood up immediately and stuck his arm straight out in front of him wit palm facing to da side.  He den began to spin slowly.<br>
<br>
"What are you..." a confused Medsa began to ask.<br>
<br>
"Blip..." said da ranger. "Blip... Blip... Blip...." da ranger repeated as he slowly spun in da clockwise direction.  Den, he began saying da word faster as his arm stretched in a southern direction. "Blip Blip Blip Blip..." He finally stopped and was facing a bit southwest. "Bliiiiiiiiiiiip!"<br>
<br>
Da ranger got a smile on his face and den was racing off in da direction at a break-neck pace.<br>
<br>
Da group sighed in frustration.<br>
<br>
"Me wish he would start letting us know when he gonna take off like dat!" exclaimed an irritated Bash.  Da udders agreed and dey all ran off after da ranger.<br>
<br>
---------<br>
<br>
Dey eventually came upon a copse of trees and saw what dey was looking for.  Dere was Lilting, covered in dried mud, struggling wit all his might to break free of da grip of a large treant.  Da big treant not even seem to notice dat Lilting was trying to get free.<br>
<br>
"Let me go, barkface!" said Lilting.  Da treant not even seem to hear.  She continued to cradle da halfling and rock back and forth while singing her lullabye.<br>
<br>
"Rock a bye baby in the treetops..."<br>
<br>
Da party looked on wit disgust and horror.<br>
<br>
"We've got to save the lad!" said Yessir in a loud whisper.  "I'll go in and slay that thing that reminds of a dragon!"<br>
<br>
"No!" whispered Bash.  "Us not want to fight a treant.  Especially a protective mother-type.  Us need to figure out what to do."<br>
<br>
"She thinks Lilting is her baby?" asked Pyra.<br>
<br>
"It look dat way," said Bash.<br>
<br>
"Well, what should we do?" asked Treehugger.  "I found the guy, but that's pretty much all I'm good for.  I can't fight that thing because I'll get killed!"<br>
<br>
Nobody knew what to do.<br>
<br>
Eventually, Medsa spoke up.  "Why don't we just find her real baby?"  Everyone turned to  da cleric.<br>
<br>
One by one, each party member slapped deir forehead.<br>
<br>
"Ok, let's see if I can track that thing," said Treehugger.  "Radar signals get very jumbly in this area since there are so many crossed frequencies with all the druids around here tracking.  I'd need a general direction."<br>
<br>
Bash looked at where da treant was sitting.  Next to her was a cradle.  By da cradle, where some bird-like footprints dat lead off to da west.<br>
<br>
"Me is no expert tracker," said Bash, "but me is wondering if dose footprints have anyting to do wit da kidnapping?"<br>
<br>
Treehugger looked at da big ogre amiably.  "I think you've got it, Bash!  Let me test it out."<br>
<br>
Da ranger stuck his hand up in da direction da footprints led and said, "Blip Blip Blip Blip Bliiiiiiiip!"  Da ranger smiled.  "Yep!  Let's go!"<br>
<br>
------<br>
<br>
Birdbrain da aviak sat high in his treetop home.  He looked at da treant child and laughed to himself which sounded berry much like clucking.  His partner-in-crime, Egghead, stood closeby scheming.<br>
<br>
"Cluck cluck cluck, BickAww cluck!" said Egghead, which was Aviak for "<i>We're going to be rich!</i>"<br>
<br>
"Cluck!" said Birdbrain, which was aviak for "<i>Darn tootin' we are!  It is conceivable that that treant female will pay handsomely to us whether in gold or magical services!  We shall be kings amongst birds!  Hail to us!  Hail!  Hail!</i>"<br>
<br>
"Cluck cluck cluck cluck cluck, Bickaww, cluck cluck cluck hoot hoot cluck whipperwhil!" said Egghead, which was aviak for "<i>w00t</i>!"<br>
<br>
Just den deir friend Chickenlegs burst into da room at blinding speed.  Slamming da door behind it, da bird began speaking out of breath, "<i>Look out... *pant*... someone is onto our scheme.... *pant*....  they're coming</i>!"<br>
<br>
"<b>CLUCK!</b>" yelled both Egghead and Birdbrain which was aviak for.... well.... me can't say because it not a nice word.  Just know it showed dat dey was both angry and frustrated.<br>
<br>
"<i>How long do we have</i>?!" asked a panicked Egghead.<br>
<br>
He needed no answer.  For just den, someting massive slammed into da door wit a thunderous cracking sound.  Da birds looked at each udder wit eyes wide open in terror.  <br>
<br>
Da wooden door flew apart into many splinters as a giant hammer slammed into it a second time.  A monstrous, naked ogre forced his way into da room and roared.<br>
<br>
"<b>CLUCK!</b>" screamed da three petrified birds.<br>
