<p><b>Chapter 23.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Da aviak treehouse was ransacked by da enraged ogre.  Not much was left except all da molted feathers flying around from da many terror stricken aviaks.  Bash even destroyed da stereo system dat was playing da annoying John Tesh music da aviaks seemed to enjoy so much.  Dere was much cheering from all da druids who was camping at da bottom of da treehouse.<br>
<br>
Bash came running back up to da place where Lilting was being held against his will.  He carried someting bundled up in a blanket.  Treehugger looked at ogre and gave him a silent nod.<br>
<br>
Da group watched as Bash went into da clearing, somewhat out of sight of da treant, and unwrapped da blanket.  Dey no could see what was in da blanket from where dey was.<br>
<br>
"Mama!" cried a tiny voice in da direction of Bash.  "Mama!  Mama!"<br>
<br>
"Baby?" a confused mommy treant said.  "Baby?" she said again while looking at Lilting.<br>
<br>
"Mama!" da voice cried.  Bash was sure to get out of da way and headed back to where da party was hiding.<br>
<br>
"Baby!" da big treant screamed while dropping Lilting and running to whatever it was dat Bash brought back.<br>
<br>
Treehugger was quick to run in and snatch da halfling before anyone was da wiser, including Lilting.  <br>
<br>
Da big near-sighted treant screamed wit joy when she found da ting she had been looking for all along.  She picked up her baby and cuddled it close.<br>
<br>
"Mama!" said da baby.<br>
<br>
Da group finally was able to see da treant's child.  It was a baby Hill Giant.  Dey all looked at each udder and shrugged.  At least da baby and mommy was happy once again.  Bash sniffed back a tear.<br>
<br>
"It's about freakin' time!" said a high-strung Lilting.  "Where the Hate were you guys?!  Do you have any idea what the Hate it's like to be snuggled against by a thing whose skin is made of rough bark?!  Gaaah!!"<br>
<br>
"Us is sorry, Lilting," said Bash apologetically.<br>
<br>
"You better be!  And where's your clothes?!  And what was the deal with your hammer?!  And what was...."  Lilting stopped in mid-sentence.  His eyes became distant and glazed.  Without a word, he spun around and bolted away from da party.  Da halfling waved his hands and his feet sped him up even faster.<br>
<br>
Everyone just stared in shock and confusion at da distant halfling.<br>
<br>
"Well, I guess we better follow the idgit," said da Paladin.<br>
<br>
-----<br>
<br>
Grizzleknot da treant was feeling good today.  He didn't like to venture out into the open much, but today felt different.  He felt alive and good about life.  So much, dat he felt like singing.<br>
<br>
"Doo bee doo bee doo bee dee doo," sang da treant.  "Well it's a doo ba dee doo, I mean a doo ba dee doo, I mean a doo bee doo bee doo bee doo ba dee doo!<br>
<br>
"It's a.... hey!" at dat moment a halfling druid had leapt out of some nearby bushes and attached itself to Grizzleknot's leg.  It den began pounding at da treant wit its fist.<br>
<br>
"Hey now, little britches!  What's the big idea?"  da treant began.  But just as he did, two more halflings came running up from different directions and jumped and landed on an arm and his back.<br>
<br>
"What's going on here?"  <br>
<br>
Four more halflings came running up and jumped and latched on to da treant.  More halflings were seen running up behind dem.<br>
<br>
Grizzleknot was starting to have a hard time standing up wit all da halflings on him.  Dey was grabbing his neck and his waist, everyting.  He started to fall down.  He saw even more halflings coming his way.  One was a little odd, he thought, because it was covered in dried mud.<br>
<br>
-------<br>
<br>
Da group saw where Lilting had went when dey caught up.  Dere, standing three stories high, was a giant mound of halflings piled on top of each other.<br>
<br>
"How are we going to find him now?!" shouted a frustrated Medsa.  "I say we ditch the guy."<br>
<br>
Just den, da group heard some peoples trotting up behind dem.  A troll, a barbarian, and anudder ogre came lumbering up as fast as dey could.<br>
<br>
"Chococake heard that Grizzleknot was around?" said da barbarian.  "Chococake wrong?  Can you tell Chococake where he is?"<br>
<br>
Da troll looked like it was deep in thought and then pointed to da halfling pile-up.  "Deyz iza ona Grizzy dere!"<br>
<br>
Da ogre, troll, and barbarian ran up to da pile and roared.  All da halflings scattered in every direction like dey was cockroaches when da lights come on.  On da ground, dere was da skeleton of a treant.<br>
<br>
"Ahhhh.... dang it!!!" da three shamen screamed aloud.<br>
<br>
Bash saw da halfling he was looking for running in a direction similar to where he was at.<br>
<br>
"Oh no yous don't!" said da ogre as he grabbed da halfling and hoisted it into da air.  Lilting legs were still moving wit effort like dey not knew it dey wasn't on da ground anymore.<br>
<br>
Lilting had a frenzied look in his eyes and his teeth gritted a piece of bark dat he apparantly had torn from da treant.  <br>
<br>
Bash smacked da halfling upside da head.  Lilting's face returned to normal.  Bash grabbed da bark from his mouth.<br>
<br>
"Sorry about that," said da halfling.  "I don't know what came over me.  I just had this overwhelming urge to..."<br>
<br>
"Save it," said da ogre.  "Right now, us have overwhelming urge to kick yous tiny butt!  Let's get to Halas."<br>
<br>
"Right-o, my boy!" said Sir Yessir.<br>
<br>
And wit dat, dey all followed Yessir to da northwest.</p>
