<p><b>Chapter 25.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Bash just stared at da demon, frozen in pure terror.  He had never known such fear before.  He could easily see da demon's fangs were stained wit blood while it smiled wickedly.  He watched as da demon unfolded its massive black wings to deir full extension.<br>
<br>
"<b>So you're the one that I've been looking for</b>," da demon said in an otherwordly growl.  "<b>Pity.  I expected you to be much bigger, much more intimidating, and much more.... clothed.  No matter, you will die today in any case.</b>"<br>
<br>
Da demon let out an ear-splitting roar and den charged Bash.  Cloven hooves digging into da ground, da demon moved wit lightning speed towards da ogre.  Killdead slammed his shoulder into da ogre and sent Bash flying into da air.<br>
<br>
Killdead laughed as da ogre landed wit a <i>CRUNCH</i>.  He knew his fun was just starting.<br>
<br>
Pyra screamed at da demon after watching her two friends be tossed about like rag dolls.  She sent two fireballs flying towards da demon.<br>
<br>
Killdead turned just in time to see da balls of flame hurtling towards him.  He did nothing to stop dem.  Da fireballs slammed into his body, and da demon didn't even blink.  Da conjured spheres of fire did not even phase da demon.<br>
<br>
"<b>Fool!  Do you really think such primitive spells could harm me?!  I've let you all live for too long.  Now the killing begins!</b>"<br>
<br>
Da demon ran towards Pyra wit sword raised and ready slam down into da wizardess.  Da demon came into striking distance and swung his sword right towards da lady's head.<br>
<br>
Treehugger came running up behind Pyra and leapt over da wizardess and put both his swords up in a cross formation while in mid-air.  Da demon's sword collided wit da ranger's and it sent da force sent da ranger flying towards da ground.  Treehugger's body slammed partially into Pyra and da wizardess was sent into a daze and laid on da ground.<br>
<br>
But da ranger was quick and jumped to his feet.  He whipped his swords up towards da demon and let out a snarl and his eyes filled wit rage.<br>
<br>
Treehugger called out, "Medsa!  Go tend to Bash and Yessir!  Now!  Lilting, help me take this sucker down!"<br>
<br>
Da cleric quickly nodded and ran off to Bash and Yessir.  Treehugger's eyes never left da demon.  Da demon's eyes stared back, glowing even hotter wit rage.<br>
<br>
"<b>So it will be you who will die first today</b>," da demon growled.  "<b>Tell me ranger, will you still be so courageous when I am torturing your soul for an eternity?</b>"<br>
<br>
"I guess you'll just have to find out!" yelled da ranger as he sliced his shortsword towards da demon.  Da demon blocked it wit his massive black claymore and den swung it  towards da ranger's head.<br>
<br>
Treehugger easily ducked underneath it and rolled towards da demon.  He spun upwards and  chopped at da demon.  His swords bounced off  da demon's scaly hide doing berry little damage.  He leapt back in surprise.<br>
<br>
Da demon grinned at da ranger.  Den it lifted up its sword, roared, and charged.<br>
<br>
Treehugger parried the forthcoming blow and sent two more Killdead's way.  The two combatants were now locked in intricate swordplay.  For every thrust there was a parry.  For every parry, there was a swing.  For every swing, there was a block.  For every hack, there was a dodge.<br>
<br>
Medsa reached Yessir first who was just coming back to consciousness.  He sat up blinking.  Da cleric casted a quick refreshing spell dat let him come to his senses quickly and den she was off towards Bash.  Yessir saw da fight between ranger and demon and immediately stood up.  He ran towards da battle wit rusty sword raised.<br>
<br>
Da demon swung his claymore downwards towards da half-elf again, and Treehugger brought his swords up in an X shape once again.  Da swords banged into each udder, and den just stopped in place.  Killdead pressed downwards on his sword and Treehugger did his best to push back wit his swords.<br>
<br>
Da ranger was losing da test of might.  He was going to be forced off his feet soon.  And probably would have had not a halfling appeared on da back of Killdead.<br>
<br>
Lilting climbed up da demon's backside quickly and stood on its shoulders.  Den da lil guy screamed, "Booot to the head!" and kicked da side of da demon's head wit all his halfling might.  Dis distracted da demon enough to let Treehugger jump away from da demon.<br>
<br>
Killdead howled wit rage and grabbed da halfling wit his free hand and tossed Lilting away from him.  Da halfling floated gently to da ground.  Treehugger sprang back into the demons range wit swords flailing.<br>
<br>
Medsa reached Bash and revived him wit a spell.  Bash sat up and blinked.  He saw da battle his friends were having wit da demon.  His friends were losing.  He didn't know what to do.  <br>
<br>
"What are we going to do, Bash?!" pleaded a frightened Medsa.  <br>
<br>
"Me no know," said Bash wit a frown.  "Me no kn...." Bash's hammer flared and became hot to da touch again.  It glowed a brilliant white.  "Wait.... me have idea."<br>
<br>
Da demon's sword nicked da ranger now and den spilling bits of da ranger's blood here and dere.  Nothing worse dan scratches, da ranger was skilled at avoidance.  Treehugger did his  best to dish out as much damage as he was taking, but da demon's scaly hide prevented him from causing much hurt to Killdead.<br>
<br>
Pyra started to come out of her daze and turned to see Treehugger locked in combat wit da demon.  Da ranger's swords were moving so fast dat dey was just a blur.  She started to stand up to try and help.<br>
<br>
Yessir ran as hard as he could.  He hoped he could get to Treehugger as quickly as possible to lend some muscle to their side.  He saw da two swordmasters in a perpetual dance.  If he could just get dere quick enough...<br>
<br>
Treehugger started to feel the strength leave his body.  Da toll of his fighting began to set in.  Killdead noticed his opponent was becoming slower.  He knew his chance was coming soon.  It was inevitable, he knew.  No mortal could ever hope to defeat him.<br>
<br>
Treehugger swung into da demon one more time.  Killdead swung his sword wide and hard and forced Treehugger's own swords to swing wide.  His midsection exposed, da demon swung his free hand and clawed at da ranger.  Treehuggers stomach was split wide open.<br>
<br>
Da rangers eyes went wide and just stared into da distance.  Da demon smiled.  Da ranger fell to his knees, still staring at nothing.  His swords fell to da ground, and den da ranger fell over backwards.<br>
<br>
Medsa turned to see Treehugger just as he fell to da grass limply.  She screamed.  "<b>NOOOOOOOOOOOOO!!!!!!!!</b>"</p>
