<i>Posted by Numbuk on 10-13-2000 09:54 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p><b>Chapter 28.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Emerging from da other side of da cave, da party just stared in wonder and awe.  Dey had never seen snow before. Well, none but Yessir, who recounted tales of how he slew three snow dragons in one single day.<br>
<br>
Snow covered everyting in dis mountain canyon dey was in.  Rocks, trees, mountains, nothing was untouched by dis cold, white substance.  <br>
<br>
"The one thing I don't get," said Lilting, "Is that how can it get so cold over here when it's like 80 degrees just on the other side of the cave?"<br>
<br>
"Shhhh!" da party shushed.<br>
<br>
"Or what about that desert we went through," da halfling started again, "How did it go from hot humid swamp to dry arid desert  in just a blink?"<br>
<br>
"Shhh! Da gods might hear you!" Bash said.  Da last person he knew dat questioned da gods was an ogre shadowknight friend of his.  He had questions and sought answers, but one day he woke up wit no intelligence.  Dey said he only had enough brain cells to breathe, eat, and blink.  Bash never forgot his friend whose name was Nurphed.<br>
<br>
While pondering on his friend Nurphed and anudder friend who had disappeared from dis world altogether, Bannedfur Good, someting hit da ogre like a ton of troll casserole.  It was cold!  It was berry cold outside!  Freakin' cold!  Bash was suddenly berry aware  of his naked ogre body.  He started to freeze all over, from his head, to his feet, to his jumblies*.<br>
<br>
"Guys..." Bash said shivering, "Dis starting to suck.  Me need clothes!  Bad!  Let's get to dis Halas place soon!"<br>
<br>
Yessir lead da way through the cold slush and ice.  Overhead da clouds moved in and blocked out da afternoon sun.  It den began to snow.<br>
<br>
Dey came upon a fork in da canyon road.  Yessir became puzzled.<br>
<br>
"Hmmm.  I don't remember this place having a fork in the road." da paladin mentioned confusedly while rubbing his stubbly chin.  "Hmmm.  Maybe we'll go this way."<br>
<br>
And da party took da right fork.  Dey came upon anudder fork shortly after.  And anudder.  And anudder.<br>
<br>
"This place wasn't this maze-like before!" da paladin exclaimed.  But den he asked himself under his breath, "Was it?"<br>
<br>
Da party was so turned around dat dey didn't even know which was up anymore.  No sun could tell dem where north was, and da only tings Treehugger and Lilting could track was demselves.  Finally, dey came out in a big snowy clearing.  About a hundred yards ahead dey saw a gigantic frozen river.<br>
<br>
Bash's skin was now purple.  He was so cold his brain started to tink he was warm.  His whole body was numb.  He just wanted to lay down and go to sleep.  Den he saw two figures wave at him from a distance.  He didn't know if dey was real or not.  Da figures den started running towards him and he finally saw who it was.<br>
<br>
"Nnnnn.... Nnnnnn....." Bash chattered trying to talk.<br>
<br>
"What is it, Bash?" asked Medsa.<br>
<br>
"Nnnnnn.... Nnnnneeee...." da ogre tried to say.<br>
<br>
"What do you see?" asked Pyra.<br>
<br>
Da party strained to see what Bash saw.  Several seconds later dey saw da figures for demselves.<br>
<br>
"Nnnnnn.... Nnnnnecro!"<br>
<br>
Up came running a snow-covered Philiac followed by his skeleton friend Jakontiklarkiak.<br>
<br>
"Hi guys!" da gnome said cheerily.  "Cold enough for you?"<br>
<br>
Da skeleton just waved at da group.<br>
<br>
Bash wanted to pick up da gnome and chomp him, but he was too cold to even do dat.  So he just gritted his teeth in a big grimace.<br>
<br>
"I was studying how snow looks, so that, you know, when Hate freezes over I'll be sure to know!  You remember our deal, right?"<br>
<br>
Bash just grimaced some more.  <i>Tink happy thoughts, Bash.  Tink happy, warm thoughts.</i> thought da ogre.<br>
<br>
"Oh yeah!  I almost forgot!  Come see what I found!  Hurry!" da gnome was off running back towards da frozen river.<br>
<br>
Da skeleton shrugged at da party and was off running after his master.  Da group slowly and reluctantly followed.<br>
<br>
Bash couldn't keep up wit da group.  His limbs were almost gelatin.  He saw his friends step out onto da river and look dowanrds at to someting Phil was pointing at.  Den dey looked up at Bash, and den back down at da ice.<br>
<br>
"Bash," shouted Lilting, "I think you better come look at this."<br>
<br>
Bash made it to da river and looked to see what everyone was staring at.  He looked down.<br>
<br>
Dere, frozen in da ice wit eyes open wide and  mouth in a timeless scream, was an ogre dat appeared to look just like his brother Smash.<br>
<br>
