<p><b><img src="images/icons/icon5.gif" alt="Question" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p><b>Chapter 29.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Bash just stared at da frozen ogre wit puzzlement and shock.  Could dis be his brudder?  Could dis be...<br>
<br>
"Smash?" da big ogre asked quietly to da ice-ting.  Obviously, it no responded.<br>
<br>
Bash's friends just watched silently.  Dey felt sorry for da big guy.<br>
<br>
"Smash!" shouted Bash.  "Help me get him out of here!  Please!"<br>
<br>
"Bash," said Medsa, "I'm still very weak from healing Treehugger.  Even if you got him out I don't think..."<br>
<br>
"Us have to try!  Please help me get him out here!"<br>
<br>
Shivering from being almost frozen to the bone and also from being so shaken up over seeing his brudder, Bash lifted up his hammer and began slamming it into da ice.  He repeatedly hacked away trying to break up da thick, frozen sheet.<br>
<br>
Lilting pulled out his tiny, tiny, ultra-tiny dagger and ran up beside Bash.  He bent down and started chipping away at the ice to help his big friend.  <br>
<br>
Phil joined in too.  He came up next to Bash and started jumping up and down on the ice in the hopes to break through. Following his master's lead Jakontiklarkiak started jumping up and down alongside the gnome.<br>
<br>
Da rest of da group sighed and started helping deir friend.  Everyone was chipping away what dey could.  Da person who gave da most help was Pyra.  She sent out a stream of flame dat spewed forth from her fingers like a blow-torch.  Da ice started to melt away quickly.<br>
<br>
Bash noticed da ice around da ogre was melted enough.  Slush covered da face of what he thought may be his brudder.  He signaled everyone to stop.  He took his big hand and brushed away da snow-cone like ice remains and took a look at what dey uncovered.  Bash began to sob.<br>
<br>
What appeared to have been an ogre trapped in ice was nothing more than a large, brown rock.  Everyone's eyes went downward feeling bad for da ogre.  Dey knew he missed his brudder very much.<br>
<br>
"Me should have known," sniffled Bash.  "Me should have known he not be here.  Why would Smash go to Halas?  Why would..."<br>
<br>
Da ogre stopped.  He looked to his side and noticed dat Phil was still hopping up and down like mad.<br>
<br>
"We'll get that ogre out!  We'll get him!" da gnome chanted as he leapt up and down and slamming as much force into da ice as his tiny body would let him.<br>
<br>
All of a sudden, da ice underneath Bash's feet began to crack.<br>
<br>
"We'll get your brother out Smash!" said da necromancer.  "Don't worry!"<br>
<br>
Treehugger saw what was happening.  "Phil!  Stop!  Don't jump anymore!"  Da ranger just looked on as da gnome didn't seem to hear him and da ice began to crack some more.<br>
<br>
"Stop, Phil!  Stop" each person started scream.<br>
<br>
"Don't worry guys!" da gnome said again unaware of da warnings being shout at him.  "I'll rescue that ogre! I'll...."<br>
<br>
Da ice underneath Bash and Philiac gave out.  Both the gnome and the ogre were immediately plunged into da icy river.  Da party just stared in surprise and horror as dey saw da forms of deir friend and gnome acquaintence get pulled underneath da ice by da river's strong current.  Da two bodies could be seen moving at a great speed under da thick ice sheet dat covered da rest of da river.<br>
<br>
Jakontiklarkiak looked at da group, shrugged, and den hopped into da newly made ice-hole.<br>
<br>
"Now that," Sir Yessir said, "Is why I'll never group with a necro.  They never listen."<br>
<br>
-------<br>
<br>
Bash's mind was racing.  He knew he was being pulled somewheres at an alarming speed.  He knew he was in someting berry, berry cold.  And he knew dat if he tried to breathe, he would die.<br>
<br>
He tried his best to grab onto someting as his body zoomed by large, icy, underwater outcroppings.  His hands were so numb dey couldn't get a firm hold onto any of da slippery surfaces.<br>
<br>
He eventually gave up trying to struggle and faced da fact dat he was gonna die.  He prayed dat his brudder would one day find his way back to Oggok.  He prayed dat Smash had found Smellybreath and bashed him real good.  He started pray some more when his body slammed into someting berry hard.<br>
<br>
Bash realized he had come upon a rocky bank.  He mustered what strength he had and tried to climb out of da river.  He plopped himself onto da stony ground, sat up and realized he was in an underwater cave.  Not five feet away fom him was Philiac lying unconscious, face-first in da gravelly rock.  Bash sneered at da gnome.<br>
<br>
Den da ogre felt someting hot on da back of his neck.  Bash spun his head around and saw, just inches from his face, da muzzle of da biggest, meanest, white-est, bear he ever saw.  Three times da size of da ogre, it was.<br>
<br>
Da bear roared at Bash.  Our hero, overcome with fear, fatigue, and hypothermia, passed out.</p>
