<p><b><img src="images/icons/Dizzy_Face.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p><b>Chapter 30.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
"The time has come, my Elemental Guardians," Smellybreath said while standing atop his small altar, "To set in motion my grand design.  You four are but the first step."<br>
<br>
Da four black knights stood motionless in front of da goblin wizard.  Each of deir swords glowing as brightly as da day dey was created was in each knight's hand.  Fire, Ice, Earth, and Air these dark warriors were named and deir bladed weapons glowed brightly da color of each respected element.  If dey could speak or not, only Smellybreath knew.  If dere was actually someting inside da ebony armours, only da goblin knew.<br>
<br>
"It was very difficult in acquiring these, but well worth it.  Here, each of you take one."<br>
<br>
Da goblin reached into a pouch he had on his belt and pulled out a single, polished, shiny, black, oval-shaped stone.  Da stone had a single white rune symbol on it.  He handed it to da first and biggest black knight, Fire.  Da black knight closed his fist around da stone and stood back at attention.<br>
<br>
Smellybreath den did da same for da udder knights until each had a single stone of deir own.  Da goblin grinned wickedly when his presents were passed out.<br>
<br>
"Now, using these stones is simple.  If you trace the rune one way with your left index finger, it will teleport you to a destination I have predetermined for each.  If you trace it the opposite way, it will teleport you back here.  Any questions?"<br>
<br>
Da knights just stood stock still, full helmets just staring straight ahead at da goblin.  Smellybreath chuckled to himself.<br>
<br>
"Good.  Now, go.  And when you arrive at your  destinations unleash vengence.  <b><i>My</i> vengence!!</b>"<br>
<br>
Eeach knight simultaneously banged deir clenched sword hand against deir breastplates.  Da room was filled wit a resonating <i>CLANG!</i>  Each knight put deir swords in deir magical scabbards and den traced da different patterns on deir stones.<br>
<br>
A whirlwind of colors swarmed around each individual knight.  Then colored lines raced up and down each of deir bodies.  A bright flash briefly appeared and den each knight was gone.<br>
<br>
Smellybreath smiled evilly, each pointed tooth clearly visibile in da light of da torches surrounding his altar. <br>
<br>
"And so begins the prophecy..." da goblin said to himself.<br>
<br>
-------<br>
<br>
<br>
"What should we do?!" pleaded Lilting.  "We can't go after them!"  Da halfiling looked across where da frozen river ran where he saw his ogre friend disappear out of sight.  Lilting sniffled back some tears.<br>
<br>
"I....  I don't know." said Treehugger.  Frustration, anger, and sorrow welled up inside da ranger.  He slammed his sword deeply into da ice out of rage.<br>
<br>
"There isn't a thing we can do, lad." da old paladin said.  "But that doesn't mean there isn't a thing <i>anyone</i> can do about it.  Let's go talk to the barbarians.  They skinny dip in this thing all the time, like it's some sort of test of manhood.  I bet they may know where Bash ended up."<br>
<br>
"Test of manhood," snorted Medsa.  "Sounds more like a test of idiocy."<br>
<br>
"You'll find that those two things are often one and the same, my dear lady." Yessir said wit a smile.  "Come, I think I can remember the way to Halas.  Follow me."<br>
<br>
And wit dat, Yessir trekked off into da snowy hills wit da group in tow.<br>
<br>
