<i>Posted by Numbuk on 10-18-2000 11:41 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/icon4.gif" alt="Exclamation" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p><b>Chapter 31.</b><br>
<br>
<br>
Dan YellSan was one of da best monks in his class.  He lived in Qeynos wit all da udder monks.  He spent many years training berry hard to get where he is today.  He mastered every move dere is in da Book of Chan, da monks' bible.  He most recently mastered da "Hold Fists in Front of Self, Shiver and Shake With Rage, and Scream Waaaah!" technique.  He currently waited in the "Room of Patience" just outside his master's dojo.<br>
<br>
Dan YellSan's sensai, Mee YahGee, was quite proud of his student.  Today, in his dojo, he  was going to present da black belt to his finest pupil.  He was quite confident dat Dan YellSan could face any opponent and be victorious.  This was the price of 25 years of hard work, training, discipline, and doing odd jobs for Mee YahGee.<br>
<br>
"Dan YellSan, come here!" shouted Mee YahGee while he stood in da middle of da wooden dojo.<br>
<br>
Dan came running and bowed before his teacher.  He stood up and met his sensai eye to eye.<br>
<br>
"Show me, San-Do-Floor!" exclaimed Mee YahGee.  Dan started spinning his arms in huge concentric circles.  Mee started quietly giggling.  Dan YellSan always fell for that and still believed it was of any use in da battlefield.<br>
<br>
"Dan YellSan, you have achieved great rank amongst the monks.  You are deserving of this."  Da old man held up a folded belt of black color.<br>
<br>
"Thank you sensai," said Dan wit a bow.  "I will do my best to...."<br>
<br>
Dan YellSan was cut off by screaming outside.  He and his sensai looked at each other and immediately bolted to da door and went outside.  If dere was someting looking for trouble, dey was gonna find it wit Dan YellSan and Mee YahGee.<br>
<br>
What dey saw horrified dem.  Da streets were completely covered red wit running blood.  A dark figure was slashing monks left and right and ripping through dem like dey was tissue paper.  To get to udder peoples, it would crash through houses and den throw limp bodies outside.<br>
<br>
Da dark figure came closer to where Dan and Mee stood.  It slashed more monks along da way until it stood right in front of Dan YellSan.<br>
<br>
"Dan YellSan!" shouted Mee YahGee, "The Crane!  If do right, no can defense!"<br>
<br>
Dan nodded and put his arms up in a 'Y' formation and lifted one foot off da ground.  Whoever dis ting was, Dan was sure it finally would pay for da deaths of his friends.<br>
<br>
Da dark being looked at Dan and den swung its  sword downward towards da young monk.  Dan YellSan was split into two symmetrical vertical pieces.<br>
<br>
Mee YahGee just stared in disbelief. "But... but he did right...  No can defense!"<br>
<br>
Mee YahGee looked at da big black ting in front of him.  He could see dat it was a knight, at least seven feet tall.  His eyes trained downward to da bright, glowing, white sword da knight held.  Mee YahGee took up an offensive stance.  It was time to show dis ting what an old monk can do.<br>
<br>
Da big knight made no advance on da monk.  Instead, it thrust its sword downward into da ground.  A blast of hot air shot out from all around da knight.<br>
<br>
Da wave of air slammed into Mee YahGee, throwing his body into da air at such a high speed dat it sent him flying for miles.  Da air continued outward from da knight totally destroying anyting, building or person, in its path.  Da blast wave died out about one hundred feet from da knight.<br>
<br>
Air, da black knight, pulled his sword from da ground and turned around to continue his carnage.<br>
<br>
-------<br>
<br>
Norrath had just begun to feel da wrath of Smellybreath by his guardians.  Da black knight, Earth, was seen ripping apart da underground dwarf city of Kaladim.  No dwarf was safe from dat black knight as he chopped, sliced, and fileted dwarves by da dozens.  Occasionally da knight would cause massive earthquakes dat brought many of da beautiful earthen structures down killing many more.<br>
<br>
Ice was seen in da High Elven city of Felwithe.  Elves were instantly frozen in deir tracks and den shattered into millions of tiny pieces wit a swing of a sword or a punch of a black gauntlet.<br>
<br>
Smellybreath could feel his anger manifested through his guardians as each scream echoed in his tiny, green ears.  He could feel each soul taken away from the mortal plane.  Da prophecy da goblin knew about was indeed coming to pass.  He would make everyone pay for what dey did to him.<br>
<br>
Soon, he would become so powerful that none would be able to stop him.  This he knew, and this he planned.</p>
