<i>Posted by Numbuk on 11-02-2000 12:03 AM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/icon5.gif" alt="Question" width="15" height="15" border="0"> Chapter 35.</b></p>

<p>Bash stood in da middle of a large, dark room.  Torches hung upon da big stone walls, but still not giving off enough light for da ogre to see much.  In da center of da room was a tiny, circular altar wit weird symbols and runes etched all over.  Da arcane letters gave a small amount of light of deir own, pulsating slowly.<br>
<br>
"Where in da...?!" said da ogre aloud.  His sentence was cut off by someone behind him.<br>
<br>
"I am so glad to see you.... my son." da familiar voice said.  Bash spun around and became face to face wit his father and mother.<br>
<br>
"Mudder?" asked Bash quietly.  "Fadder?"<br>
<br>
"I knew you'd make it!" said Mommy Emgood.  "We knew you were strong."<br>
<br>
"Yes, we did," said Daddy Emgood.  "We cannot stay long.  We just wanted to tell you that we love you and..."<br>
<br>
"...and that we don't think you should kill another life just to avenge our spirits." Mommy Emgood finished his father's sentence.<br>
<br>
"Yes," began Daddy Emgood.  "Forget about the goblin, son.  We're proud of you no matter what you do.  We know you love us.  Please, just leave the goblin alone.  We don't want to lose you too."<br>
<br>
"Take care, son." said Mommy Emgood.  "Remember that we love you!"<br>
<br>
Bash's parents suddenly began to become transparent and den dey disappeared.<br>
<br>
"Mama!  Dada!" shouted Bash.  Bash let loose some tears quietly and thought about what had just happened.<br>
<br>
Bash became confused.  He spent da last several years of his life waiting to smush dat dumb goblin's head in.  Now his parents come out of nowhere and tell him....<br>
<br>
Atop of a flight of stairs in da room, a door opened.  A lone figure's shadow was seen against da light and den stepped into da room.  Bash recognized who it was instantly.<br>
<br>
"Smellybreath!" whispered da ogre.<br>
<br>
Da goblin no seemed to notice da ogre and stepped onto his altar.   He pointed both hands straight above him and began chanting in a language Bash never heard before.<br>
<br>
Da ogre's face contorted wit rage.  He felt his hammer flare up.  He felt da need to see goblin brains splattered all over da room's walls.<br>
<br>
Bash ran up as fast as he could behind da goblin and quickly raised his hammer to end da miserable ting's life in one blow.  Da goblin heard da ruckus behind him and spun around to see dis massive ogre wit hammer held high above its head.<br>
<br>
Smellybreath couldn't scream.  It just looked at da ogre wit surprise and fear.  Eyes wide open and jaw agape, all he could do was shake his head in a "No! Please!" manner.<br>
<br>
Bash's hammer felt white-hot.  It wanted blood.  It wanted goblin blood.  Da ogre knew it, and wanted it too.  He screamed.  In da middle of his scream, dough, he remembered his parents.<br>
<br>
His hammer made him quickly forget what his parents said and just as quickly reminded him of what happened to dem in da first place, and just who caused it.  Da ogre swung his hammer downwards.<br>
<br>
In dat split second of da hammer's swing, Bash thought again to his parent's wishes.   As his hammer arced down into da perfect curve dat would connect it to Smellybreath's soft head, da ogre pulled wit all his strength to divert its course.  Da hammer just barely missed da goblin and swung wide.  Da force from his swing ripped da hammer out of his hands and sent it flying into da wall.<br>
<br>
Da hammer ripped a hole through da stone and purple light poured into da room from it.  Bash felt da floor begin to shake beneath him, and den saw da whole castle room begin to crumble.  Stones started falling from da ceilings, and da walls collapsed upon demselves.<br>
<br>
Smellybreath, along wit his altar, vanished before da ogre's eyes.  Bash was so confused at dis point, he no thought about his own safety.  Da whole castle began to fizzle, and den pretty much disappear all together.<br>
<br>
Da ogre saw nothing but purple.  He was standing on someting solid, but could no see it.  Da color purple permeated all throughout his surroundings.  Nothing else seemed to exist.<br>
<br>
"Well done, Moondoggy!" said a voice from, again, behind da ogre.<br>
<br>
Bash spun around, again, and dis time was face to face wit Papa Smurpheater.  <br>
<br>
"Grandpa!"  exclaimed Bash excitedly.  "What in da Hate just happened?!"<br>
<br>
"You passed the test, hip cat!"<br>
<br>
"What test?" asked Bash confusedly.<br>
<br>
"THE test.  The test the armor had to perform to make sure you were worthy of wearing it!  An evil heart cannot wear such a piece, and it had to know if your heart was filled with nothing but vengeance."<br>
<br>
"Me see..." said da ogre, not totally understanding.  "Where is dis place?"<br>
<br>
"This?  This is the place few visit other than in dreams."<br>
<br>
"So da goblin, da castle and......." Bash began to choke back some tears. "....and me parents...?"<br>
<br>
"Not real, lovemonkey.  Sorry about that.  It had to feel real to you, or the test wouldn't have been accurate, man.  You're not even here.  Only your mind is."<br>
<br>
"Are yous real?"<br>
<br>
"You better believe it, nature boy!  I'm here, just not physically, man!"<br>
<br>
"How....?"<br>
<br>
Da old ogre pointed to a jar of someting he was holding.  Bash recognized it as da Sacred Peyote.<br>
<br>
"What about what me parents said.... about not smashing dat goblin?  Me not allowed to smash dat dumbhead?"<br>
<br>
"Well, those weren't your real parents.  At least, I'm pretty sure they weren't.   I think you've proven to the armor that you wouldn't kill him if you were told not to.  And since it now knows you're not in this thing only for revenge, I think it's plausible you can beat the crap out of that little bugger."<br>
<br>
"Dat good!"<br>
<br>
"But anyways, Moondoggy, you have to get back.  Your friends are in danger, or will be soon.  The oracle should be able to get you to them.  Take care, my little one.  I love you, man!"<br>
<br>
"Me love yous too, grandpa."<br>
<br>
Bash hugged his grandpa tightly and sniffed back some more tears.  Me hope he no cry like baby all throughout story, it embarrassing to write about.  Anyways, he sniffed back some tears and den his world suddenly faded to black.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
