<i>Posted by Numbuk on 11-09-2000 12:29 AM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/Hmm_Face.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> Chapter 36.</b></p>

<p>Smellybreath stood outside on da battlement of his castle, high above da ground.  Da goblin surveyed da surrounding area and let out a sigh of contentment.  All around him thick, grey fog blanketed everyting dat he could see.  But da goblin could see more dan just what his eyes told him.  He felt da surrounding dead trees, he sensed da rocky, black earth beneath da castle, he tasted da setting sun.<br>
<br>
"All will look like this one day," da goblin said quietly to himself.  "All will be paradise.<br>
<br>
"Lousy, good for nothing, Alcoholics Anonymous friends." muttered da goblin.  "Laughing at me saying my plans for world domination would never happen."<br>
<br>
Smellybreath chuckled to himself.  He took in da wonderful, black/grey site once more and den turned around and headed back into his castle.<br>
<br>
Da goblin walked down many stairs until he reached da heart of his home, da underground chamber dat housed his altar.  Da goblin stepped atop it, placed his feet on two particular types of runes, raised his arms up high, closed his eyes, and began chanting.<br>
<br>
Da whole castle started to shake ever so slightly.  So miniscule was da vibration dat most wouldn't notice it.  However, it didn't stop dere.  Da castle began to quake more and more violently wit each passing moment.  It started shaking back and forth so hard, dat torches were flung from deir holsters across da room.<br>
<br>
Smellybreath kept his balance, kept his eyes shut tight, and continually chanted in some acient, arcane tongue.  Da castle was quivering so much now, it was if it were in a giant's grasp and he thought dat da castle was little plastic globe dat 'snowed' when you shook it.<br>
<br>
Just as quickly as it started, da castle's shaking stopped.  All was quiet outside.  Da fog still rolled past, da sun still no gave any light anywhere around.  No birds chirped.  And had one been able to get a good look through da fog, one would see dat da place where Smellybreath's castle used to be on da mountain was now no more dan a huge, empty crater.<br>
<br>
----------<br>
<br>
<br>
"But we need to see your chieftain!" demanded Treehugger.  He and da group were outside da barbarian city dat was located in da heart of da icy mountains of Permafrost.  Da barbarians didn't welcome outsiders much.<br>
<br>
Two guards stood outside da city, not allowing da group to pass.  As a rule, barbarians always wear kilts and nothing else.  Da bare chested guards had blue war paint on deir faces, and stood shivering in da snow.<br>
<br>
"Nnnnnn...No.  BBBBarbarians only.  NNNnnnn nnnn No one sees Chief except Barbarians." da guard said as he stood at attention.  His teeth began chattering.  Da udder guard's teeth were locked in a grmaced grit.  Each gaurd's skin was red from being exposed to extreme cold.<br>
<br>
"Don't you boys think you should wear a jacket or something?" asked Pyra.<br>
<br>
"Nnnnnnn.... Nnnnnoo!!  Jacket is wwwww...wwwweakness!  BBBBBBarbarians.... strong!!"<br>
<br>
Da udder barbarian nodded his headed slightly and quickly.  His mouth never moved and stayed locked in a grimace.<br>
<br>
"Bah!  Enough of this, lads." exclaimed Yessir.  "They'll not give us any trouble.  They can barely move.  Follow me!"<br>
<br>
Da paladin marched between da two frozen guards.  Da first paladin raised his arm slightly as if to protest, or maybe try to use force, but his arm locked up and became motionless.  Da barbarian just chattered his teeth and shivered while his eyes followed da party as dey walked on by.  His udder guard friend, just stood staring straight ahead, still in his perma-toothy-smile.<br>
<br>
Finding da Chieftain's hut was not hard for da party.  Da barbarians would do deir best to point dem in da wrong direction, but dey was so stupid dey always point in da exact opposite way which da hut was located.  Da group found deir way to da hut wit little problem.<br>
<br>
"Why for you come to Chief Hardnipple's city?!" shouted a big, angry barbarian man standing in da middle of da hut da party just entered.  Da barbarian was barechested, just as da rest of da males, (to Yessir, Treehugger, and Lilting's disappointment, da females were not topless).  He had blue war paint all over his body, supposedly in articulate designs, but looked like dey was painted on by a toddler.  "Chief Hardnipple is not happy you have come to Chief Hardnipple's city!"<br>
<br>
"I thought this guy <b>was</b> the Chief?" whispered Lilting to Yessir.  Da paladin just shrugged.<br>
<br>
"Where is your Chief, good barbarian?  We've an important matter at hand!" said Treehugger forcefully.<br>
<br>
"Chief Hardnipple says you are speaking to Chief Hardnipple!  Chief Hardnipple does not like you being here!"<br>
<br>
Treehugger figured it out.  Da chieftain spoke in da third person.<br>
<br>
"Chief, please hear us out.  We need your help.  A friend of ours fell into your river of ice and we don't know where he is or how to..."<br>
<br>
"Chief Hardnipple says SILENCE!  Chief Hardnipple does not see you worthy of barbarian acknowledgeme.... acknow.... Well, you know what Chief Hardnipple means.  Chief Hardnipple says you must prove to Chief Hardnipple that your blood is that of a barbarian!"<br>
<br>
"All of us?!" asked Lilting.<br>
<br>
"Chief Hardnipple says, Yes!  All of you!  Chief Hardnipple says that if you...."<br>
<br>
Chief Hardnipple was cut short.   Outside dere came a sound of a gigantic explosion.  Screams broke out from somewhere outside da hut.  Everyone in da Chief's hut looked surprised, including da Chief.  Just den, a big chunk of wood debris came ripping through da hut's roof and landed right next to Lilting.  Da piece of wood was on fire.<br>
<br>
Da party ran outside and saw smoke billowing up from da center of town.  More screams were heard in dat general direction and most were cut unexpectadly short.<br>
<br>
A gigantic ball of flame exploded from somewhere in da center of town, setting more barbarian homes ablaze.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
