<p><b> Chapter 38.</b></p>

<p>Fire came towards da group while dey just looked at him wit deir moths and eyes wide open.  None of dem could move.  None of dem believed dat moving from da knight would help dem anyway.<br>
<br>
Da black Guardian moved closer and closer to da party, wit sword glowing brighter dan ever.  Da knight reached Medsa first.  Fire raised its sword arm to do da killing blow to da caleric.  Da high elf just bowed her head and closed her eyes in sorrow dat she could do nothing for her friends and wished dem all a quick death.<br>
<br>
A sound made da knight pause in confusion.  It was a voice, and it came from behind da Guardian.<br>
<br>
"Hey...  Dumbhead!"<br>
<br>
Da Elemental Guardian lowered its arm and turned at da sound.  Medsa opened her eyes and watched da knight turn around at dis new sound.  She no could see over da knight, but she did catch a glimpse of a huge, huge hammer twirling quickly, stopping, and den swinging fast to connect wit da knight's helmet.<br>
<br>
A loud <i>*CLANG!*</i> resulted, and da knight was hit so hard dat it spun in place.  It stopped and doubled over onto  one knee.<br>
<br>
Dere, standing behind da knight, was an ogre.  Clad in an armor dat looked like it was dipped in pure platinum, he held aloft his shiny matching hammer, ready to smash it into da knight again.  Da group recognized dis new savior.  It was...<br>
<br>
"BASH!" shouted Lilting.  "You're alive!"<br>
<br>
"Yup!  But dis guy no is for long!"<br>
<br>
Da black knight quickly shook its head violently to remove da stun from da hammer.  It got back to its feet quickly.  Standing upright, da Guardian was easily da same size as da ogre.<br>
<br>
It looked at Bash and cocked its head as if confused slightly.  Instead of making an attack, it immediately went for someting in its black belt.  <br>
<br>
Bash watched wit curiosity as da knight rapidly sheathed it's sword and pulled out a small, gleaming black stone wit a white rune on it.  He watched da knight trace his left index finger from da bottom to da top of da symbol, making sure to follow every line and curve.<br>
<br>
Da knight den vanished in front of dem all in some sort of dimensional gate.<br>
<br>
"And don't come back!" said da ogre.<br>
<br>
Medsa, Pyra, and Lilting rushed da big ogre.  Dey all each hugged da big ogre (one on each leg, while Lilting hugged a knee cap).  Tears were streaming down everyone's face.  All was quiet except for da loud snort-sobbing of Lilting.<br>
<br>
All was quiet until a roar of cheering erupted from da many hiding barbarians who witnessed Bash getting rid of da terror dat ruined half deir town.  Barbarians came from all over da place to slap da ogre on da back and continued to cheer.<br>
<br>
"What going on?" asked Bash.<br>
<br>
"That knight you killed destroyed their town!" said Medsa.   "He also.... he also."<br>
<br>
"He hurt Treehugger and Yessir." Pyra said solemnly.<br>
<br>
"Where is dem?  Can we help dem?!"<br>
<br>
"I can probably heal their wounds, but I'm afraid... I'm afraid I can't do anything for Yessir's leg." Medsa told da ogre.<br>
<br>
"What happened to his..." da ogre began but was cut off.  He saw Sir Yessir hopping on one foot.  Half of da paladin's right calf had been lopped off below da knee.  Interestingly  enough, da noble knight didn't seem too upset by it.<br>
<br>
"Now that fellow," said Sir Yessir, "Was the second meanest fellow I've ever met!"  Da knight muttered someting about da first being some dumbhead dark elf named Giz or Gix or someting.<br>
<br>
A scream of pain and ultimate suffering rose up among da noisy barbarians.  Out of some rubble stumbled Treehugger.  Da ranger held his swords, well, what were formally his swords, in his two hands.  Dey had been melted into nothing more dan hilts.  Da ranger wailed as if he had just lost all of his family in an explosion.<br>
<br>
"Us need to get Yessir fixed up." said Bash.  "Who here can help us wit dat?"<br>
<br>
"I'm betting that big Chief Hardnipple can!" said Lilting excitedly.<br>
<br>
Da ranger wailed some more.<br>
<br>
"Ok den," said Bash.  "Let's go see him.  Where he at?"<br>
<br>
Da group went back to da chieftain's hut, wit Yessir hopping behind and Treehugger walking slightly slower crying and pouting and wailing all da way.  Da biggest line of barbarians hooted and hollered behind dem as dey followed dis great party toward's deir tribal chief's home.</p>
