<p><b> Chapter 39.</b></p>

<p>"Chief Hardnipple is saying thank you for saving Chief Hardnipple's city!" said a very grateful chieftain to da group standing before him.  Dey was standing in da chief's berry large hut.  Da barbarians was uncomfortable being around da big ogre, and Bash mutually shared dat feeling, but da big humans knew well enough just who had saved deir snow covered town.<br>
<br>
"Mr. Hardnipple, sir, I have a question." stated a concerned Sir Yessir.<br>
<br>
"Chief Hardnipple is saying ask what you wish of Chief Hardnipple."<br>
<br>
"It's about my leg, Mr. Hardnipple.  Might I be able to get something to stand on?" da paladin asked his question while hopping on his good foot to keep balance.<br>
<br>
Da chief looked at one of da barbarians standing right next to him and nodded.  Da barbarian was off and running out of da hut.  "Chief Hardnipple will be taking care of that!"<br>
<br>
Bash wondered what da chief was up to to help his friend.  Da ogre soon realized a sound was coming from behind him.  It got louder and udder peoples in da room noticed it too.<br>
<br>
It was sound of crying and phlegm being snorted back at da same time.  Bash stepped aside and dere was Treehugger clutching his melted swords to his chest.<br>
<br>
Chief Hardnipple frowned in confusion at da ranger.  Medsa just shook her head and sighed.  "You big baby!" she said.<br>
<br>
Treehugger just looked at her, looked at his swords again, and just started wailing even louder dan before.<br>
<br>
"Can't you do anything to shut him up?" Pyra asked looking up to da chieftain.<br>
<br>
"Chief Hardnipple would do anything to get wussy human elf to zip lip!  But Chief Hardnipple is not sure what Chief Hardnipple can.... wait.  Chief Hardnipple may have an idea."  Da chief looked at anudder barbarian standing next to him and nodded.  Den dat barbarian bolted out of da hut at da same speed da first one ran.<br>
<br>
"Anyway, since you have saved Chief Hardnipple's village, by barbarian law you must each marry one of Chief Hardnipple's daughters or sons by tomorrow morning!  If you don't Chief Hardnipple will see it as an insult and comdemn you to death!"<br>
<br>
Each one of Bash's group got a real uncomfortable look on deir faces.  Lilting began to squirm uneasily.  Bash frowned.  Pyra got sick.<br>
<br>
Da chief had a straight face, but den started to snicker.  Den he and his barbarian friends burst out laughing.  Dey laughed REALLY loud.  "Chief Hardnipple is saying he is joking!  Chief Hardnipple says you should have seen the looks on your faces!"<br>
<br>
Da whole group heaved a sigh of relief.  Da laughter died down as da two barbarians da chief had sent away came back wit blankets under each of deir arms.  Da blankets were obvioulsy each wrapped around someting.<br>
<br>
"Ah, here are Chief Hardnipple's loyal subjects!  Let us and  Chief Hardnipple be seeing what they have, shall we and Chief Hardnipple?"<br>
<br>
----------<br>
<br>
Dark fog.  Dat was all dat surrounded dat black castle.  It slowly moved around da castle, seemingly penetrating da black stone like it didn't exist.  Da only sound heard was violent screaming coming from somewhere inside da structure.<br>
<br>
<b>"WHAAAAT!!?!?!?!?"</b> screamed Smellybreath to da big, black knight, Fire.  "Are you SURE you saw what you saw?"<br>
<br>
Da Elemental Guardian slowly nodded its horned, helmeted head.<br>
<br>
Smellybreath turned away from da knight and began to think aloud to himself.  Da goblin tapped his tiny green fingers together methodically.<br>
<br>
"An ogre in True Totemic?  That in of itself is a bad sign.  But even worse it's an Emgood.  I was hoping that the ogre with the party was just your average, stupid ogre.  But noooo, that never happens!  Do I ever get my way?  Do I?!"<br>
<br>
A bird flew past da window on da wall da goblin was facing.  Smellybreath instantly pointed and shot a magical beam of energy at it.  Da bird was instantly fried in magical fire and den floated to da goblin's hand.<br>
<br>
"I'll get my way this time," da goblin said as he bit da head off of da bird.  "Oh, I will indeed."<br>
<br>
Da goblin spun around to face da big knight.  "It is time.  Begin phase two of my plan!"<br>
<br>
Da black knight nodded, banged its fist against its breastplate's chest, and den pulled out da teleport stone it carried.<br>
<br>
Da knight was gone moments later.</p>
