<i>Posted by Numbuk on 12-20-2000 10:41 AM:</i>

<p><b> Chapter 40</b></p>

<p>Da sun was high in da sky and shone down brightly on da Northern Plains of Karana.  Bash's armor glinted and reflected da light all over da place.  Da ogre was a sight to behold!  Local residents and bandits alike had to stop to watch da strange and curious vision go by.<br>
<br>
Da ogre was not da only odd ting.  Behind him marched a funny erduite wizardess who kept shooting small balls of flame at da woodland creatures as dey passed.  Behind her zipped a hyperactive halfling dat kept running circles around an annoyed looking high-elf.  Behind her trailed two more peoples, one a scruffy old paladin wit a wooden stump in da shape of a boot on one leg who made squeaky noises as he walked; and da udder was a ranger who's eyes were wide open and had a smile like a little kid wit a new toy, for he had two shiny shortswords in each hand and was twirling dem by da hilt in huge circles.<br>
<br>
"Will you stop that?!" blurted Medsa almost screaming at Lilting.  She gave da halfling a look dat would have made fire turn to ice.<br>
<br>
"I can't help it!" said da halfling.  "I'm just too happy!  Too happy!  Too happy I am!  Bash is back!  Woo hoo!  Bash is...."  Lilting found dat his feet were somehow rooted to da ground and he no could move anymore.  He saw magical sparklies fade from Medsa's hand.  "Hey!"<br>
<br>
"And you," said Medsa looking back at Treehugger, "Will you stop with the whirling and twirling already?!"<br>
<br>
"I can't help it!" said Treehugger.  "These swords are just so cool!  They're lightweight, yet stronger than anything I've ever held!  And look!  Look!  See that?  On each blade there is a barbarian warrior locked in battle with a monster etched on the metal!"<br>
<br>
"I know!  I've seen it!" exclaimed Medsa who apparently was a bit high strung.  "You've only been showing us for the past two days!"<br>
<br>
"Yeah, I know.  I just like it when you get mad though.  Your face gets flushed and your eyes get wide so it makes it easier to see how pretty and brown they are."  Da ranger winked at da cleric.<br>
<br>
Medsa just sneered at da half-elf and faced forward away from him.  She wouldn't let him see it, but she was blushing and trying her best to keep her lips from curling into a grin.<br>
<br>
"Ye know," said Sir Yessir not really paying attention to anything, "This wooden boot actually is better than my real foot!  It's not nearly as painful to walk on.  There's no arthritis, corns, athletes foot, and this weird green fungus that burned.  I think I like it!"<br>
<br>
Da whole party shuddered wit revulsion at da mental image da paladin just gave dem.<br>
<br>
"So where are we headed, Bash?" asked Pyra.<br>
<br>
"Freeport.  Da oracle told me of a hermit dat lives out on an island in da ocean dat may have some information to where we need to go to find Smellybreath.  And since Freeport has da only boats dat can sail out into da ocean, well, me guessin' us gonna have to go back dere."<br>
<br>
"Guuuuuuys!" a faint voice shouted dat sounded not too dissimilar from Lilting.  "Wait up!  Come on!  I can't move!"  Da halfling's feet finally came free and he ran as fast as his tiny legs could to catch up.<br>
<br>
<br>
-----------<br>
<br>
Smellybreath sat on his throne tapping his fingers on one of da armrests.  Da goblin could feel <i>their</i> presence and waited patiently for dem to come.  How dey got here, he didn't know.  But he was confident dat dey would not stay long.  Da goblin thought to himself, "<i>Here they come.  Three.... two.... one...</i>"<br>
<br>
Da door to da goblin's inner room where his throne and altar was blew apart from some magical force.  In poured dozens of peoples all wit berry shiny armors and all carrying weapons dat had sparklies running up and down dem, or swords made of fire.<br>
<br>
"Hail a Smellybreath Goblin!" said da person at da front of da group.  He did not look too happy to see Smellybreath.<br>
<br>
"I will ask you this once and only once," said da goblin.  "How did you get in here?"<br>
<br>
"How?  How?!  What do you mean, <i>how</i>?!  I am Uber Boober, guild leader of the Flames of Heaven(tm)!  We can do anything and go anywhere!  We are always the first to do so!  Our ShowDToT Linux users have told us that you are a new spawn in this world and are very high level.  We have come to destroy you!"<br>
<br>
"You all must be powerful indeed if you come here boasting to kill me without even the slightest hint of fear amongst any of you."<br>
<br>
"We have spent our entire lives becoming powerful!  We're all just nerds who have nothing better to do with our time other than focus it all into fighting big stuff like you and getting cool weapons and armor!  We are betting you drop some nice phat l00t, so therefore you must die!"<br>
<br>
"You really think that I will give you something that will help you rule the world?"<br>
<br>
"Of course not!  In fact, we'll probably just sell what we find on your carcass for about 100,000 platinum pieces!  We just want to be the <b>first</b> to get it, have the picture of it up on the "internet" and have everyone else bow down before us because of our awesome power!  So prepare to die!"<br>
<br>
Smellybreath yawned.  "I grow tired of this.  Since you are all so powerful, you probably will be the only ones to ever figure out how to reach my castle.  This makes me much more happy.  It was nice knowing you, I guess."<br>
<br>
Da goblin outstretched his hands and shot forth a red lightning bolt.  It arced through Uber Boober and den spread out shooting through everyone else in da Flames of Heaven(tm) guild.  An instant later, everyone in da guild was shrunken down to about an inch high.  Da goblin waved his hands again and all da guild members floated up into da air and was pulled towards da goblin.  Da goblin held out a bowl and everyone was deposited inside.<br>
<br>
Smellybreath looked down at all da tiny peoples in da bowl in his lap.  "You guys like being the first of everything, eh?  Well, here's something you may like.  You will be the first of the races to see what my stomach looks like from the inside."<br>
<br>
Da goblin grabbed a handful of peoples and den shoved dem into his mouth like popcorn.  Smellybreath chewed a little bit, swallowed, dan den spit out some tiny, tiny breastplates.<br>
<br>
"Now, let's see how my Fire Elemental Guardian is doing."  Da goblin waved his hand in an arc and in da air in front of him came da image of Fire standing in front of a big lake.  "Good, good.  He's progressing nicely."<br>
<br>
Smellybreath grabbed another handful of peoples and den sat back to watch da show.<br>
<br>
<br>
