<i>Posted by Numbuk on 12-21-2000 06:24 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/icon3.gif" alt="Lightbulb" width="15" height="15" border="0"> Chapter 41.</b></p>

<p>Fire stood at da edge of da Lake of Ill Omen, facing da body of water.  Orange claymore blazing in da knight's right hand,  Fire stood quietly waiting for someting.  Behind da Elemental Guardian were several hundred goblins glanced nervously about.  It was obvious dey no wanted to be dere, but none of dem seemed to attempt to leave for some reason.<br>
<br>
Fire raised it's sword high into da air for all da goblins to see, and den with a quick motion, slammed da blade into da lake water.  Da sword glowed even brighter dan before and a massive hiss was heard for many kilometers as steam started to rise from da lake.  A giant cloud of white steam began to pour straight up from da water itself, and da lake rapidly began to drain.<br>
<br>
As da lake became nearly empty, one could see many, many halfling druid "farmers" scatter in  multiple directions like roaches under a light.  Da water was soon no more and all dat was left were several hundred Bloodgill Goblins staring back at da knight whom had just been spending deir entire lives living underwater.  Da knight pointed at dem, and motioned dem to follow in a not-too nice way.  Da goblins not wanting to anger such a ting dat could destroy a lake so easily reluctantly marched on after da knight.<br>
<br>
Fire turned and headed eastward to da Sarnak fort.  Goblins of all sizes marched on after deir new leader, some obviously exicted about what da Guardian had just done.  It was only a matter of time before Fire emerged from da fort holding da Sarnak King by da scruff of his neck.  Da king looked like all Sarnak, in dat he was a brown lizard-man like creature wit a beak dat looked like a vulture's.  Da king hissed at da knight, but da knight silenced him by grabbing da Sarnak's tongue and sliced it off.  Da king wailed in pain and da knight ordered him to follow.  Da king went from an angry to a submissive posture and den motioned to all his Sarnak followers in da area to follow where da knight lead.<br>
<br>
<br>
------------<br>
<br>
<br>
After a few sleep-deprived nights (Lilting found a sugar cane plant and ate it.  Da halfling had such a buzz dat he no would settle down for two days), da party reached West Commons.  Da open, grassy field shone brightly in da mid-morning sun.  Dey were almost at deir destination:  Freeport.  As dey walked on, some of da group were engaged in casual conversation.<br>
<br>
"So tell me, good paladin, just what entails in killing a dragon?" Treehugger asked Sir Yessir out of curiosity.  Da group overhearing da ranger's question quieted down and listened intently to hear what da old knight had to say.<br>
<br>
"Well, that's a good question, my boy!  Dragons are tricky, evil creatures.  I have dispatched many, but I would have to say that the most common way of dispatching them is by slicing them in half!  Sccchhhhhht!  Nice and clean."<br>
<br>
Treehugger puzzled at da thought of dat.  "How do you accomplish that?!  Do you set up some great elaborate trap, with a gigantic metal blade, that the dragon stumbles upon?"<br>
<br>
"Oh dear me, no!  That would take too much time!  No, I generally run the dragon down on foot, find it, raise my sword and strike!  They will usually be cut in half in one or two swings."<br>
<br>
Bash gave a questioning look to Pyra.  Lilting gave da same look to Medsa.  Treehugger's eyebrows furrowed downward in complete confusion.<br>
<br>
"Look, my boy, if I can find a dragon nearby I will show you!"  Yessir was off searching some nearby shurbbery.  Da whole group stopped to watch dis strange, puzzling sight.  Trehugger turned around to face da group and raised his eyebrows as if to ask, "What da Hate?!"<br>
<br>
A shout of triumph sounded out from da paladin as he was bent over in one of da bushes.  "Ah ha!  I found one!  Taste, Holy Steel, dragon!!"  Out scurried a tiny gecko lizard.  It ran for its life as da paladin chased it down.  It was a sight indeed as da lizard peddled away from da big, clunky, squeaky old man.  Da old man was quick dough, and caught up to da lizard.<br>
<br>
"Your vile taint will poison this land no more, dragon!" shouted da knight as he lifted his sword high into da air.  Yessir slammed his sword downward and sliced da poor, tiny lizard in half.  He den raised both arms into da air and shouted as loud as he could, "Victory!  Victory for the Holy Order!"<br>
<br>
Bash was completely stunned at what he just saw.  Da big ogre just got a really bad feeling about dis whole mission.  "Who found dis guy again?"<br>
<br>
Da udders in da group said in unison, "Lilting!" and each of dem turned deir heads towards da halfling.  Yessir was too far away and busy praying to da gods he believed in to notce what was going on.  Lilting's eyes shifted left and right quickly and began wringing his hands in nervousness.<br>
<br>
"I... uh....." stammered da halfling.  "I... I listened to him!  He sounded like he was a real dragonslayer to me!  I just... I just wanted to help."<br>
<br>
"I should have known," said Medsa.  "The man has 'crazy' written all over him!  Now what do we do?"<br>
<br>
"Dere not much us can do.  Me said he could come, and me word is final.  Us will just have to take care dat he no gets us killed!  Maybe us can find some nice temple dat will take care of him on our journey."<br>
<br>
Da paladin squeakily approached everyone.  "Well, what did you think of that display of bravery?  I don't see as many dragons as I used to, so my blood is pumping a lot harder than it used to!  There is no rush like there is dragon hunting!"<br>
<br>
"Uhhh.... yeah." said Treehugger.  "That was... that was great!  You sure are the best 'dragonslayer' we've ever seen.  Right guys?"<br>
<br>
Everyone slowly nodded with raised eyebrows and grimaces.<br>
<br>
"Well then," said Yessir, "let's get moving!  We should try to get to Freeport before the sun sets!"<br>
<br>
<br>
-------------<br>
<br>
<br>
As dey trodded on through da grass fields of West Commons, da group saw some interesting tings.  One odd sight was a small band of dark elf adventurers attempting to fight a big, nasty Hill Giant.  Da group was no doing so good.  Da adventurers tried furiously to hack away at da giant's shins, but da giant no seemed too pleased about dis.<br>
<br>
Da giant eventually picked one of dem up, and hurled him as far as it could.  Da adventurer disappeared into da horizon.  Da giant cocked its foot back and booted da remaining elves.  Da dark elves went flying in various directions, but all were sent soaring away at a tremendous speed.  Da giant just laughed and den jogged away.<br>
<br>
"Well that was entertaining!" said Treehugger aloud.  "Stupid, no-good dark elves!"<br>
<br>
Just den dey heard a cry for help off into a small cove of trees.  Da group ran over and saw dat many trees were knocked over, most likely from da giant.  Da cry for help came from a very well-dressed dark elf standing near a felled log.<br>
<br>
"Oh please, good adventurers!" pleaded da dark elf.  "Will you please help me?  Neriak's Royal Prince is trapped under this log!  He will surely die if you do not save him!"<br>
<br>
"Let the guy rot, I say!" said Treehugger.<br>
<br>
Bash wasn't so sure.  His grandpa told him to help everyone.  Even someting inside him told him dat leaving anyone to die is not befitting a shaman.  Bash almost swore it was his armor telling him dat.<br>
<br>
"No, us will help.  Lilting, please help me.  Cast a levitate spell on dat log so dat me can lift it easire."<br>
<br>
Da halfling sighed and began casting his spell.  Bash sidled up to da log and began lifting it.  Da ogre could hear faint muttering underneath da log.  Lilting's spell kicked in and da ogre heaved da heavy log over his head.  He den tossed it to da side.<br>
<br>
Underneath was a dark elf clad in colorful silk robes.  It stood up and began speaking in a strange tongue non of da group could understand.<br>
<br>
"tH4/\/kS, Sux0R!" said da dark elf.  "j00 r /\/0t 2 b3 0w/\/3d t0d4y!"<br>
<br>
"What the Hate did he just say?" asked Lilting.<br>
<br>
"Forgive his highness," said da first dark elf.  "He, like most of our kind, only speaks Tier'Dal, which is dark elven to you.  The only Tier'Dal, dark elves, who speak common are Court Advisors and Ambassadors.  I am the prince's court advisor.  The prince wishes to royally thank you for saving his life."<br>
<br>
"Well, dat sound good!  Me glad us could help."<br>
<br>
"s|-|ut uP, 1D10t!" said da prince.  "pH33r /\/\y l33t h4X0r \/\/r4th!!!"<br>
<br>
"The prince wishes to extend his gratitude some more and says that if you ever visit Neriak you would be welcomed guests."<br>
<br>
Da prince den turned to Medsa and began speaking.  "|-|3y b4By!  u l00k |-|0t!  u w4/\/t 2 cyb3R?"<br>
<br>
"Erm, the prince wishes to tell the lady that she looks exceptionally radiant this morning and that he is honored to be in the presence of such beauty," da court advisor said.<br>
<br>
"Well, thank you good sir!" said Medsa with a blush.<br>
<br>
"w00t!  4 w|-|0r3!" said da prince.<br>
<br>
Treehugger didn't look to happy about someone else giving her compliments.  "Well, let's get going guys.  We're glad we could help you.... elves out.  Let's get to Freeport before the sun sets."<br>
<br>
Da group set off towards da east and towards Freeport.  Da two dark elves got up and headed north-westward back to da kingdom of Neriak.<br>
<br>
"0w/\/3D!" shouted da prince.<br>
