<i>Posted by Numbuk on 01-11-2001 10:13 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/Book.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> Chapter 42.  (Da answer to Life, Universe, and most Everyting)</b></p>

<p>Smoke rose from da still smoldering rubbled buildings and collected high in da sky.  Da once beautiful city had been decimated by some unknown force.  Rock walls dat "protected" da city were stained black from some obvious recent fires and in udder places were completely blown apart.  It had been just fine when Bash last left it, but now da city of Freeport was nothing more dan a wasteland.<br>
<br>
Bash stood on da hill just outside da city gate and no could believe his own ogre eyes.  Humans were cleaning up as best dey could, but it was apparent dey had been doing so for days.  Even bodies still littered da ground and da people were still trying to take care of dem and get dem to a proper burial ground.  Many peoples were on deir knees wailing and sobbing, probably for da loss of a home, loved one, or both, da ogre thought.<br>
<br>
"Whoa," whispered Lilting.  "What happened here?"<br>
<br>
"Me not sure," said Bash.  "But me have pretty good idea."<br>
<br>
"Our friend from Halas?" asked Treehugger.<br>
<br>
"Dat is what me is tinkin'" Bash said solemnly in a low tone of voice.  <br>
<br>
"I've been meanin' to ask ye," said Sir Yessir.  "Just what do ye think that thing was and what was it doing?"<br>
<br>
"Me have no clue.  But me would bet all me shares of stock in eqBay dat Smellybreath is behind it all.  Just what he is doing, well, dat is what us is trying to find out."<br>
<br>
Bash looked upon da wreckage of da city and all human children who is now without a mommy or a daddy.  Just like him.  All dis because of da evilness of one hateful goblin wizard.  Bash swore to himself once again dat he will kill Smellybreath or die trying.  And once again, he thought he felt his hammer flare to life for an instant just as the vow entered his mind.<br>
<br>
"Come on," said da ogre breaking out of his train of thought.  "Let's go see if us can help."<br>
<br>
Da group descended da hill overlooking da city and headed toward da now destroyed city gates.  Da grass on da hill was untouched by da fires dat had ravaged Freeport, but Bash noticed someting a little odd about all da surrounding shrubbery.  Da ogre got an uneasy feeling, and den his hammer flared to life.<br>
<br>
Out from da surrounding bushes jumped several creatures.  Da party was quickly surrounded by orcs, gnolls, goblins, and lizardmen.  Dere was about eighteen of da bad guys, overall.  Da party, mostly taken by surprise, jumped back.<br>
<br>
Treehugger's newly acquired swords instantly appeared in each hand as he pulled dem free from deir scabbards.  Yessir's rusty sword came loose from wherever da paladin kept it.  Bash, one step ahead of everyone was already in a defensive crouch.  And Lilting pulled out his tiny, tiny, oh-so tiny small dagger.<br>
<br>
"Rrackkk hrggeakkk hockkrakkk!!!" said one of da bigger lizardmen.  "Horkk Wracckkk!!"<br>
<br>
"Me no can understand yous, lizard!" said Bash angrily.  "But me bet what yous said is not good!  Us will fight yous!!"<br>
<br>
Da lizard made some more sounds.  "Hrackk... Mrmmpph....  HRACKKK!!!" and den spit a big wad of lizard loogie on da ground.  "Ahhhh!  Much better!  Stupid piece of phlegm has been bothering me since we left Cazic Thule."<br>
<br>
"Lizardmen can talk?" Lilting whispered to Bash.<br>
<br>
"Me guess.  Dey only tell Bash about how us ogres ruined our own lands dough.  Not much else."<br>
<br>
"Anywaaaay..." continued da lizard.  "Me and the guys here were told to take you out."<br>
<br>
"Preposterous!" snorted Sir Yessir.  "I do not date lizardmen or gnolls or any of the others there!"<br>
<br>
"Whoa whoa whoa!  You misunderstand me!  I mean we were told to kill you!"<br>
<br>
"Ah," said da paladin.  "That's a relief."<br>
<br>
"I'm not gay!" said da lizardman quickly.  Maybe too quickly.  "Anyways, enough chit-chat.  Let's get 'em, boys!"<br>
<br>
Some of da monsters had weapons, some didn't.  Da ones witout weapons probably no needed dem because of da claws and teeth dey had.  Already surrounding da party, dey slowly moved in closer.  Den, in da blink of an eye, dey all charged in.<br>
<br>
Da party did deir best to try and stay alive as dey were overwhelmed wit furry and scaly bodies.  Treehugger was da first to get a kill when he stuck out one of his swords and impaled a gnoll, flipped it over his head slamming it into da ground, and den swinging his udder sword overhand to decapitate it.<br>
<br>
Yessir was right behind.  Fending off a mace-wielding orc with his sword and using his trash-can lid shield to block da blows of a goblin wielding a flail.  Doing his best, da paladin seemed to be a little overwhelmed.<br>
<br>
Lilting was having worse luck.  He had to run, dodge, and duck blows dat were aimed to kill him.  He wanted to fight back, but da most it seemed he could do was scream like a little girl.  Eventually one of da orcs picked him up and tossed it to a lizardman.  Dey started playing "catch" wit da halfling.<br>
<br>
Medsa pretty much hid behind Pyra.  Not having offensive power of her own, she preferred having da protection and "firepower" of dis one-woman flame thrower.  And even dough pyra was having a little bit of trouble, da monsters facing her approached wit caution once she set a gnoll's fur completely on fire.<br>
<br>
Bash, on da udder hand, just stood dere.  Four or five monsters had come to melee range and started whacking away at da big ogre.  Since none of dem could reach higher dan his knee, and because he was well protected by his new armor, da ogre felt nothing.  He just yawned as he heard da *ting* *ting* *ting ting* sounds of da creatures below.  Bash lifted up a foot and squashed one of da orcs.  Den a hammer came down and smashed anudder.<br>
<br>
Da fight raged on, and even dough it was an uneven fight, our happy group seemed to be doing pretty well.  Treehugger got into a bit of a scrape with three orcs at once and kept getting sliced up here and dere.  But Medsa was right behind him healing him.  "'Ow! 'You're healed.' 'Ow!' 'You're healed.'" could be heard over and over in dat corner of da fight.<br>
<br>
Yessir did a decent job of holding his own.  Da paladin found it was really fun to kick da crud (literally) out of goblins wit his new wooden foot.  He was doing it quite often until da foot popped off and flew right into a goblin's face.  Da paladin didn't let it get to him.  He just dropped his shield, picked up his foot in front of da stunned goblin, and began "dual wielding" both his sword and  his wooden boot while hopping on one leg.  Amazingly enough, he killed more goblins quicker dis way.<br>
<br>
Pyra kept sending out bits of fire to anyting dat came near.  Cackling wit glee whenever she set one of da creatures on fire, she saw dat few tings actually tried to get close to her.<br>
<br>
Lilting eventually found his way to da ground.  Da druid cast some sort of spell dat slammed a gust of wind into his two assailants and knocked dem back on either side of him.  Dey both came running back.  Da halfling shrieked and hurriedly cast Spirit of Wolf on both monsters.  Da orc and lizard started running twice as fast as before and da halfling dodged out of da way.  Da two bad guys slammed into each udder hard and knocked da udder out cold.<br>
<br>
Bash was having an easy time stomping and smashing anyting dat came near.  Not much more needed to be said about him udder dan he was kicking serious butt.<br>
<br>
Anyways, to make a long story short, or a short fight long, or whatever, da group eventually killed everyting.  Dey found da first big lizard on da ground wounded from someone's sword.<br>
<br>
Bash stood over da lizard wit hammer poised.  "Any last words?"<br>
<br>
Da lizard looked up at da ogre and nodded, and den shifted his eyes over to da paladin.  "I'm not gay!!" it shouted.<br>
<br>
Bash's hammer came down and covered da grassy hill wit lizard splat.  Da group cleaned demselves up quickly and den hurriedly headed back in da direction of Freeport.<br>
<br>
"Odd," said Treehugger.  "Gnolls, orcs, goblins, and lizardmen all hate each other with a passion.  Why were they working together?"<br>
<br>
"Me don't know." Said da ogre.  "But me is gonna find out."</p>
<hr>
<i>Posted by Numbuk on 01-22-2001 10:22 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/Book.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> Chapter 43.</b></p>

<p>"This all happened about a week ago," said Mayor Fuzzywuzzy, da bald mayor of Freeport.  "Yes, about a week ago from today.  It was terrible!  Just a big black guy with this big nasty orange sword!"<br>
<br>
"That was before we met that guy in Halas," said Lilting to Bash.<br>
<br>
Da group was standing in what used to be da Council Hall of Freeport, but da ceiling had been blown off, da walls mostly reduced to tiny pebbles, and da floor marred wit black burn marks.  Da mayor was explaining what happened as best as he could remember.<br>
<br>
"Such terrible destruction of my once beautiful home town!" said Sir Yessir angrily wit a raised fist.  "Only a dragon is capable of such razing!"<br>
<br>
Da mayor rolled his eyes and sighed.  He obviously knew da knight.  "I just got done telling you what caused the damage!"<br>
<br>
"A dragon?"<br>
<br>
"NO!!"<br>
<br>
Da paladin began muttering "Still, I bet a dragon is somehow responsible."  Yessir den began speaking louder again, "I will not rest until I have slain the dragon behind this!"<br>
<br>
Everyone just moaned in annoyance.<br>
<br>
"Ok, look." said Bash.  "Us is sorry dat dis happened to yous city, and us is on a quest to make sure it will never happen again to anyone.  But us need to get to get out to an island in da Ocean of Tears.  Do yous know of a way?"<br>
<br>
"Hmmm.  A quest, huh?  Just make sure you don't take a lot of faction hits.  And, oooh oooh!  Make sure you hand in the items one at a time."<br>
<br>
"What the hate is he talking about?" whispered Treehugger to Medsa.  Da cleric shrugged.<br>
<br>
"Anyway, all of the ships that we had docked here were incinerated by that... thing." da mayor said.  "And the only  few ships we have left aren't due back for several weeks."<br>
<br>
Da whole group looked disheartened.  Dey were so close to getting da answers dey needed.  Mayor Fuzzywuzzy rubbed his stubble-less chin in deep thought.<br>
<br>
"Hmmmmm...." da Mayor said while concentrating his gaze towards da ocean.  "There <i>might</i> be a way.  It won't be pleasant though."<br>
<br>
"Us journeys have no exactly been all-yous-can-eat halfling buffet," said Bash.  Lilting winced.<br>
<br>
----------<br>
<br>
Da group stood outside a berry run-down wooden shack dat was barely standing.  If yous could even call it a shack anymore, it looked more like a pile of rotted logs.  It looked like da sightest breeze would have toppled it over.  Da shack was down da shore a little ways from da main docks of Freeport.<br>
<br>
"Man," said Lilting.  "It looks like this house took the worst of the attack of that black knight!"<br>
<br>
"No," said da Mayor, "This cabin was out of the range of the attack.  This is how it always looks."<br>
<br>
Pyra frowned.  Everyone else felt da same way.<br>
<br>
"Ok, the man in here may be able to help you guys.  He's a very, very old sea captain.  His ways are a little unorthodox, but he's your only ticket to the ocean other than a very long swim."<br>
<br>
"Sounds good to Bash!" said Bash.  "Us will gladly take all da help us can get."<br>
<br>
"All right." Fuzzywuzzy said.  "I just had to give you warning.  He's a little... odd.<br>
<br>
"Captain!" da mayor shouted.  "Captain, I say, Captain are you in there?"<br>
<br>
No sound came from da shack.  Da whole group waited for several minutes.<br>
<br>
"Maybe he's not..." da halfling began but was cut off by a shout from inside da cabin.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  Who be out there?  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"It is I, Mayor Fuzzywuzzy!"<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  The one with no hair?  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
Da mayor looked downward, almost in shame.  "Yes," he shouted.  "The very same."<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  It be a long time!  I be comin' out then to come greet ye!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"Ok guys," da mayor said quietly to da group.  "This man is very old and has seen a lot of sea action in his day.  Try not to laugh at his appearance."<br>
<br>
Everyone nodded silently.  From inside da cabin some loud noises came.  Dey were berry loud *CLUNK*s.  *CLUNK*  *CLUNK*  *CLUNK* da noises got louder and louder until da cabin door opened.<br>
<br>
Standing in da doorway was a berry, berry old man.  Older dan Sir Yessir.  Dough da captain was berry old, he still was a massive figure of a man.  Towering over all but Bash, he was still a pretty muscular fellow.  <br>
<br>
Some old sea captains had a wooden peg-leg.  Dis captain didn't have one, he had two.  One on each leg.  Not only dat, but he had peg-arms as well.  Attached at each elbow where an arm used to be was a "peg" dat looked like da ones on his legs.  Da captain had one of dose "funny pirate hats" as well, and underneath his hat he wore not one, but two eyepatches -- one over each eye.  Everyone but da mayor had deir jaws and eyes wide open at da sight.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!" said da captain.  "It be good hearin' from ye again, Mayor!  What is it ye be needin' from me this fine sailing day?  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"Captain," said da mayor, "These fine folk are needing the best sea captain and his crew to take them out to the Ocean of Tears.  Since you're the best, I naturally would have no one else even dream of the task!"<br>
<br>
"Whoa!" whispered Lilting to da mayor.  "He's the best sailor in all of Freeport?!"<br>
<br>
"No," whispered da mayor.  "He's probably one of the worst.  But he doesn't need to know that.  But he's the only one left and he doesn't like thinking he's second to anyone. Remember that."<br>
<br>
Lilting felt sick to his stomach.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  That be very kind of ye, Mayor!  I be flattered a landlubber such as ye think so highly as a scurvy dog such as meself!  Arrrgh!  I laugh at the face of danger!  I be sure I be suited to the task ye require.  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"Can you get your crew ready to sail before dawn?" asked da mayor.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  My crew be always ready at me beacon call!  That is what I be gettin' for havin' the best crew in all of Freeport!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"And how is your fine ship fairing?  I take it that it will be seaworthy by dawn as well?"<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  She be as ship-shape as the day she first lost her  virginity to the sea!  She be more than ready to set sail!  Arrrgh!"  <br>
<br>
Da captain pointed down da shore a ways to a ship tied up to a makeshift dock.  Da ship looked worse dan da cabin da captain lived in.  Da big wooden mast was leaning berry, berry far to da left (port, to yous landlovers) and it looked like it was gonna fall off any second.  Da main sail was full of holes da size of Bash's head.  Rotted wood held da ship together, just barely.  And two feet of water flooded every area of inside da ship.<br>
<br>
Almost everyone gulped.  Everyone but Bash.  Da ogre remained hopeful.<br>
<br>
"Us tank yous, captain.  Us is sure yous can help us out.  Us look forward to sailing wit yous.  Me name is Bash Emgood."<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  That be a good name fer a sailor!  Arrrgh!  My name be Captain Kirk Janeway!  Arrrgh!"<br>
