<p><b> Chapter 44.</b></p>

<p>Dawn came bright and early dat morning and da group reluctantly got out of deir beds.  Even dough da inn dey was staying at no longer had a roof... or three of it's walls... or even beds for dat matter... da group had been exhausted from da trek from Halas.  But, dey each knew dey had to get up.  For today would be deir only chance to set sail to da Ocean of Tears.<br>
<br>
Da group arrived at Janeway's docks to see a handful of burly, rustic, hairy, smelly pirates working on da ship Captain Janeway had shown dem last night.  Da pirates were busily sanding decks, taping up holes wit strips of paper and a seemingly unending supply of phlegm.  Da pirates no communicated to each udder wit words, dey just grunted back and forth and everyone seemed to understand each udder.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!" said Captain Kirk Janeway sidling up next to da group.  "I see ye be seein' me fine crew!  Arrrgh!  'Tis a good lot!  They be workin' on me ship all through the night, they be!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
Lilting had turned to listen to da captain, but den turned back to look at da boat in confusion.  Da boat looked exactly da same as it had da udder night.  And dat wasn't really a good ting.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  Lads!  Come over here and be meetin' the cargo!  Arrrgh!" da captain shouted.  Quickly da pirates jumped off da boat and lined up shoulder to shoulder so da captain could introduce dem.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh.  Gang, I'd like ye to be meetin' the finest crew these waters have 'ere seen!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
Da whole group of pirates responded wit a resounding "ARRRGH!"... except someone responded wit a high-pitched "Yay!", but none of da pirates seemed to notice or care.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!" said da captain.  "This here be my first mate and commanding officer!  Arrrgh!"  Da captain pointed to da first pirate whose face was completely covered in grey hair.  It was impossible to tell where his hair stopped and his beard began.  "Arrrgh!  This be Commander Riker McWorf!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!" da furry man grunted.<br>
<br>
Da captain den introduced da rest of da crew, who each progressively looked and smelled worse dan da last.  Dere was Tuvok Spockman da navigator, Scotty LaForge-O'Brien da engineer, Data Suluodo da logkeeper, and Bob da janitor.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  They be a fine crew, don't they?  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
Da crew returned a hearty "Arrrgh!" but, once again, a tiny high-pitched "Yay!" was heard in unison wit da crew.<br>
<br>
"Who keeps saying dat?!" asked Bash.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!" said da captain.  "Come out from behind the crew, boy!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
A mid-teenage boy weighing about ninety pounds wit brown hair and a grey sweatsuit stepped out from behind da pirates.  "Hi guys!" he said.  "Pleased to meet you!  I'm sure we'll have so much fun together!  I'm looking forward to it!  I really really am!  You bethca!  Oh boy!"<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!" da captain began.  "This be the last of me crewmembers.  He be Wussly Crusher.  Normally I wouldn't tolerate such a scrawny, annoying, nuisance on me ship but... he somehow manages to single-handedly save our ship each and every time it gets into trouble.  Quite handy to have along, he is!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh." said da pirates, but it was more of a moan.<br>
<br>
"Yep yep yep!" said Wussly.  "I am the envy of every male in Freeport ages 15 to 35!  They hate me with a passion and focus their rage on me being a whiney, know-it-all punk!  However, their anger is misplaced because in actuality, they hate me only for the fact that *I*, not they, are riding along with this crew, saving the day, and getting many, many, <b>MANY</b> hot chicks!  What a bunch of no-life, losers!  They hate me for being what they wish they could be!  They loathe me, yet still beg for me to sign their official Captain Kirk Janeway & Crew posters!"<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!" said da captain.  "If'n ye be ready, big ogre landlover, we be ready to set sail!  We best be off as soon as we can!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!/Yay!" da crew responded.<br>
<br>
"Us tink we is ready," said Bash, "but me just have one question.  How were yous able to introduce yous crew to us one at a time if yous no can see dem?  Yous got two eyepatches!"<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!" said Captain Kirk.  "It be easy!"  Da captain started sniffing loud enough for everyone to hear.  "By the smell!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
<br>
----------<br>
<br>
<br>
Da voyage on da ocean was a peaceful one.  Ok, me lying, it was not berry fun for anyone in Bash's group.  Da ship dey was sailing on seemed on da brink of falling apart, da group  found dat da pirate crew actually was capapble of smelling worse and da stink seemed to outdo itself each day, and da worst and horrible ting dat nobody could stand was da fact dat Wussly and Lilting became instant friends and were constantly talking to each udder in fast, high-pitched annoying voices.<br>
<br>
"And then there was this time," said Wussly in a hurried pace to his new friend, "We ran into this lady who gave everyone these 'games' and it turned out it was drugs!  I was the only one who didn't try these games so I ended up saving everybody!  It was cool!"<br>
<br>
"Whoooooaaaa!" said Lilting in awe.  "There was this time when we were fighting a demon and and and he was like 'Rawr!' and I was like 'Aaaaahhh!' and he was like 'You're gonna die!' and Bash was like 'No we're not!' and he was like 'Yes you are!' and I was like 'Come get some!' and Treehugger was like 'Ouch! My stomach has been ripped open!' and..."<br>
<br>
"SHUT UP!" shouted Medsa clutching her ears, obviously not able to take it anymore.  Wussly and Lilting turned to her, not understanding why she didn't enjoy their pleasant conversation.<br>
<br>
"Ohhhhh..." moaned Treehugger as he was leaning over da side of da boat.  "I remember when my stomach was ripped open... it was a wonderful feeling compared to *BLARF!*"  Treehugger had been upchucking most of da voyage.<br>
<br>
Bash stood near da boat's bow staring out into da sea.  He worried for his brudder and hoped he could find him again.  He knew dat each day he was getting closer to Smellybreath... or maybe it was dat Smellybreath was getting closer to him.  He wasn't sure.  <br>
<br>
Captain Kirk had clunked his way up next to Bash disrupting da ogre's train of thought.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  Looks like I lost the bet.  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"What bet?"<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  The bet me and me mates had as to which one of ye would be the 'comic relief who upheaves his dinner over the side of the boat the whole journey.'  Every single group of people has one, ye see.  It offsets the seriousness of the other events at hand!  I was betting the little one be the one who keel hauls his lunch!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"Oh.  Me sorry yous lost."<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  It be nothing much.  Tell me, large mate, what be so dire as to cause you to wear such a frown?  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"It a lot of tings.  Mostly it me brudder.  He disappeared a year ago and me no can find him."<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  And that what ye be doin' right now on this boat?  Lookin' for him, aye?  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"Yeah.  Me pointed in many directions, but me still no further dan when me started weeks and weeks ago."<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  Well, me and me crew will do our best to get you in the right direction!  Arrrgh!  Here is something though that I have learned through me many years:  Nothing is greater than the love of a family.  It can break steel, bend mountains, and destroy magic.  You will find yer brother again, that I be certain.  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"Me hope so," said Bash looking down at da water, staring into nothing.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!" said da captain.  "Lookee there now.  Seems we be close to our destination!  Hermit Isle!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"How da heck can yous see dat tiny island up ahead!?  Yous got two eye patches!"<br>
<br>
Da captain pointed one of his peg arms to his nose and made loud sniffing sounds.<br>
<br>
"Captain, yous is someting else." said da ogre shaking his head in wonder.<br>
<br>
<br>
---------<br>
<br>
<br>
Da ship docked at da isle a few hours later and da pirate crew began tying da boat down wit a lot of grunts and arrrghs.  Da island was pretty small, wit a lot of sand, some grass, a few coconut trees, and a tiny little hut in da center.<br>
<br>
Da group stood on da sand (well, Treehugger was propped up by Pyra and Yessir and his skin was pretty green) surveying da surroundings.  Bash was eager to get some questions answered by dis 'hermit.'<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!" said Captain Janeway standing on da plank leading to da shore.  "We will be waitin' fer ye to take ye where ye be needin' to go!  Right boys?  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh/Yay!" da crew resounded.<br>
<br>
"Well, let's get moving den." Bash said to da party.<br>
<br>
Dey came to da hut and Bash thumped on da rickety door.  A scream of complete and utter surprise came from inside da house.<br>
<br>
"*BLEEEEEEP!!!*" it shouted.  A very foul word indeed to be shouting, but it obvious da person inside is not used to visitors and especially not used to loud thumps on his door.<br>
<br>
"What the *Bleepin* *Bleep* was that?!" an old man shouted from inside da house.<br>
<br>
"Me is Bash Emgood, and me was told yous can help me out wit some questions me have!"<br>
<br>
Da door opened and in da doorway stood da scrawniest, scraggliest man any of dem had ever seen.  Da hermit was so skinny, he looked like a skeleton.  A skeleton wit berry, berry long and matted grey hair dat matched his equally berry, berry long and matted grey beard.  Da old man was berry dirty and didn't look like he had bathed for berry long time, even dough his island was surrounded by water.  Da only piece of clothing da man wore was a loincloth.<br>
<br>
"Who the *Bleep*in *Bleep* are you mother *Bleep*ers?!  You *Bleep* *Bleep* scared the *Bleep*in *Bleep* out of my *Bleep*ing *Bleep* *Bleep*!!"  Da old man was apparantly berry, berry foul mouthed.<br>
<br>
Lilting whispered to Medsa.  "What does *Bleep* mean?"<br>
