<p><b> Chapter 45.</b></p>

<p>Da group huddled close together inside da hermit's tiny hut.  Da inside of da hut wasn't much to look at.  It didn't have any windows but it had a dirt floor.  A bed made up of straw  filled one corner.  <br>
<br>
Da hermit stood against one wall and eyed da party suspiciously.  "What the *Bleep*in' *Bleep* *Bleep* do you guys *Bleep*in' want?!"<br>
<br>
Bash stepped forward, platinum armor glinting of da tiny beams of sunlight dat spilled through da cracks in da ceiling.<br>
<br>
"Forgive us rude arrival.  Allow me to introduce self.  Me is Bash Emgood..."  <br>
<br>
"And I'm *Bleep*in' Herman the *Bleep*in' Hermit!  Who the *Bleep* cares?!"<br>
<br>
Bash continued.  "Us have been told dat yous may have some information dat can help us out.  Us is looking for a goblin wizard named Smellybreath."<br>
<br>
"*Bleep*!  I can't *Bleep*in' help you *Bleep*ers there.  I've never even *Bleep*in' heard of the *Bleep*in' *Bleep* *Bleep*!"<br>
<br>
"Us is also looking for a big black knight known to cause massive destruction to towns."<br>
<br>
"Ah *Bleep*.  Now that, I know a *Bleep*in' little about.  You see, I *Bleep*in' heard that..."<br>
<br>
"Whoa, cool!" shouted Lilting from across da room.  Lilting found da only udder ting inside da hut udder dan da bed.  It was a big, black, square box wit a big, square glass lens on da front.  "What is this?!"<br>
<br>
Herman, me guess dat is his name, lost his train of thought and began talking to Lilting.  "That, is a *Bleep*in' Magic Box o' *Bleep*in' Fun(tm).  It is my only *Bleep*in' friend.  Well, that, and the *Bleep*in' Magic Console Joy Pad below it."<br>
<br>
"What does it do?" asked Lilting eyes getting bigger staring into da black screen.<br>
<br>
"I'll *Bleep*in' show you."<br>
<br>
Da scraggly hermit moved over to da big, black box and pressed a button on da front.  Da ting hummed to life and da glass 'screen' lit up in one big blue color.<br>
<br>
"Whoooooooa!" whispered Lilting.  "Is that all it does?"<br>
<br>
"*Bleep*in' hardly!"<br>
<br>
Da hermit picked up a weird looking device wit a movable stick on top and a long cord running off da back and handed it to da halfling.  Da device was attached to anudder box, dat da hermit also switched on.  Da blue screen flickered and was replaced wit tiny beings sitting in some weird, magical contraptions wit wheels dat da Magic Box called "go karts."<br>
<br>
"Press some *Bleep*in' buttons and have fun!"<br>
<br>
Lilting pressed some buttons and found he could choose to 'play' one of da tiny characters and race him around different tracks.  Lilting picked a funny, little plumber in  a red hat and blue overalls.  Da halfling sat down on da dirt floor, eyes locked on da big screen and jaw agape.<br>
<br>
Treehugger stared in amazement.  He den felt da urge to join in.  Da ranger ran over, picked up a second device attached to same box Lilting's was, sat down and chose a character to play of his own (a funny little green and white dinosaur wit a long tongue, if yous really want to know).  Da druid and ranger den went at it on screen, racing against each udder.<br>
<br>
Da hermit moved back to where he was and da rest of da group turned back to him.<br>
<br>
"Do you have any... companionship?" asked Medsa.<br>
<br>
"What?  *Bleep* No!  Who needs *Bleep*in' girlfriends when you have *Bleep*in' video games!"<br>
<br>
Bash tried to steer da hermit back to da original conversation.  "Yous were saying about dat black knight...?"<br>
<br>
"Oh yeah.  *Bleep*.  Well, I hear a *Bleep*in' thing or two from the *Bleep*in' birds who come by to rest in the *Bleep*in' trees on this island.  Turns out that some cities  on *Bleep*in' Faydwer were *Bleep*in' obliterated by things similar to what you described."<br>
<br>
"You little punk!" shouted Treehugger from across da room, his eyes glued to da magic box screen.  "What the heck was that you hit me with?! A turtle shell!?"<br>
<br>
Da hermit and da udders soon learned to tune out da bickering between da ranger and halfling.  Herman continued.<br>
<br>
"I don't know all the *Bleep*in' cities that were hit, but I do know that *Bleep*in' Kaladim was one of them.  You *Bleep*ers might want to start there.  Maybe you'll get some *Bleep*in' clues as to what the *Bleep* has been going on."<br>
<br>
"*Bleep*!" shouted Lilting as da tiny halfling pounded on da buttons of his hand-held device.  "How the heck did that mushroom make your kart go faster?!"<br>
<br>
Bash continued talking to da hermit.  "Is dere anyting else yous can tell us?"<br>
<br>
"*Bleep*.  I don't *Bleep*in' think so.  Well, other than the fact that if you don't *Bleep*in' hurry the whole world will suffer.  But you *Bleep*in' *Bleep*s alread knew that, eh?"<br>
<br>
Da group, udder dan Lilting and Treehugger, looked at each udder.  <br>
<br>
"Uhhhh... no." said Pyra.<br>
<br>
"Oh." said Herman.  "Well, no pressure!"<br>
<br>
"How the *Bleep* did you get the *Bleep* ahead of me, you little *Bleep*!" shouted Treehugger.<br>
<br>
Da ogre shook da hermit's hand.  "Us tank yous for yous time and help.  If dere's anyting yous need, us will try to help."<br>
<br>
"Some *Bleep*in' pants would be nice.  Loincloths tend to ride-up too *Bleep*in' much."<br>
<br>
Bash nodded.  "Ok," da ogre said to group.  "Let's go!  We need to talk to dem little dorfs!"<br>
<br>
Da group started to follow Bash out when Yessir noticed dat Lilting and Treehugger hadn't moved and were still staring at da black box and pounding rapidly on da devices in deir hands.  Da paladin signaled Bash.<br>
<br>
Bash looked at da two group members.  "Ok guys, let's go."<br>
<br>
Treehugger and Lilting stared at da screen as if in a trance, racing deir little characters like mad against each udder.<br>
<br>
"Guys, let's go NOW!" said Bash in a slightly loud ogre voice.<br>
<br>
"Just one minute, mom." Lilting said in a quiet, distant voice; not moving or blinking his eyes.  Da ranger and druid were neck and neck on screen and da 'finish line' was just ahead.<br>
<br>
"Dat's it!" boomed da big ogre.  Bash stomped over to where da two were and pounded on da button of da tinier box.  Da race disappeared and da blue screen returned.<br>
<br>
Da ranger and halfling screamed in ultimate pain.  "<b>NOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO!!!!!!!!!!!</b><br>
<br>
<br>
------------<br>
<br>
<br>
Da group headed back towards da boat.  Lilting and Treehugger acted as if dey was coming out of a trance wit each step away from da hut.<br>
<br>
"Wow," said Lilting.  "I can see why that hermit guy cusses so much!"<br>
<br>
"Yeah," said Treehugger.  "That thing was pretty mind controlling."<br>
<br>
"Yes I'm glad Bash turned it off."<br>
<br>
"Me too, even though I was about to win."<br>
<br>
"Whatever!  I was about to pound your sorry *Bleep* into the ground!"<br>
<br>
Da two began arguing and Bash just sighed.  Dey were approaching da boat anyway and da ogre could just lock dem below deck if he had to.<br>
<br>
"Captain Kirk," shouted Bash to da captain, who was directing minor repairs on his boat.<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!" shouted da captain.<br>
<br>
"Us need to go to Kaladim, on da tiny, wussy continent of Faydwer!"<br>
<br>
"Arrrgh!  We be ready to set sail when ye be!  Arrrgh!"</p>
