<i>Posted by Numbuk on 03-15-2001 05:45 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/Book.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> Chapter 46.</b></p>

<p>Black storm clouds raced along da sky, seemingly destroying any light dat may have once been.  Da wind wailed like a banshee screaming for someone's death.  Out of da darkness shot a lightning bolt dat lit up da sky for an instant and da silouhette of a castle was seen against da clouds.  Da bolt slammed into a spire at da top of da castle.  If anyone saw da spectacle, dey might almost swear da bolt was blood red.<br>
<br>
In his dungeon throne room, Smellybreath stood hunched over his tiny pool of dark, magical blood.  Peering into da blood, he could see through da eyes of his dark Elemental Guardians but dis was berry taxing on da goblin, even dough it would kill even da most powerful wizard outright.  <br>
<br>
Da goblin watched and a smile began to curl upon his lips.  Da smile widened into a wicked grin. <br>
<br>
"Good.  Good!  You are doing quite well, my General of Fire!" da goblin said quietly to himself.  "Keep bringing me more!  More for my army of hatred!  More for my fist of vengeance!" <br>
<br>
Smellybreath cackled wit glee.  Da goblin calmed down and waved his hand over da blood, as if to change da channel and look on another part of da world.  He den growled angrily.<br>
<br>
"Earth!  Get back here now!  I summon you!!"<br>
<br>
Within seconds, a black portal appeared and da black knight, Earth, stepped through.  Da knight banged its gauntleted fist against its dark, breastplated chest and made a slight bow.<br>
<br>
"What is going on down there?!" da goblin demanded.  "Why are you not progressing with your task as quickly as your brothers?!  My orders were simple!!" <br>
<br>
Da knight bowed its head.<br>
<br>
"Are you having trouble?  What is the problem?!"<br>
<br>
Da knight lifted its head slightly and da black helmet just stared blankly at da goblin.  It seemed as if da silent knight didn't say a word, but Smellybreath seemed to understand da evil brute.<br>
<br>
"I see.  They're tougher than they look, eh?  Well, I am a forgiving fellow.  Go back to beginning of the plan and finish what you started."<br>
<br>
Da knight banged his fist again and pulled out da teleport stone it carried.<br>
<br>
"Oh, and one more thing..." da goblin said to da knight.  Earth cocked it's head slightly.  Smellybreath raised his left hand and shot a streaming force of purple energy into da knight.  Da knight dropped to its knees and shook violently.  If it could scream in pain, it obviously would. Smellybreath just smiled as he continued to shoot out da purplish energy.  After a few more seconds da goblin stopped.<br>
<br>
Da knight jerked and fell forward, putting an arm out straight to catch itself from slamming into da ground.  Earth raised itself back to a standing position, but was still shaking from whatever it was da goblin had done to him.<br>
<br>
"...Don't fail me again." da goblin said wit a piercing gaze.<br>
<br>
Da black knight banged its chest wit a shaky fist, and hurriedly traced da symbol on its teleportation stone.  In seconds, Earth was gone.<br>
<br>
Da goblin sighed and walked over to his throne.  "I am a very forgiving fellow indeed."<br>
<br>
<br>
-----------<br>
<br>
<br>
Da midmorning sun peeked through da clouds as da ship's crew tied off da boat at da dock.  Many of da gruff pirates slapped Wussly on da back and gave a "Arrrgh!" of tanks, for Wussly had saved da ship (again) from certain destruction three times during dis particular voyage.  Bash's group descended down da ship's plank to da docks.<br>
<br>
When everyone was on da dock, Captain Janeway clunked down da gangplank to see da party off.  "Arrrgh!  I be sailin' all around this here ocean many, times I be!  But ye all be bein' the best bunch o' landlovers I e'er be seein'!  Arrrgh!"<br>
<br>
"Arrrrgh!/Yay!" Captain Kirk's crew/Wussly all shouted at once.<br>
<br>
"Us tank yous all for helping us out." said Bash.  "If yous ever need help wit anyting, me no will hesitate.  In fact, me betting me could round up a bunch of ogre friends to help yous fix up yous ship and yous shack!"<br>
<br>
Da captain looked confused.  "Arrrgh!  What's wrong with my ship and my house?  Arrrgh!"  Janeway's crew looked at each udder and shrugged in confusion as well.<br>
<br>
"Uh... apparantly nothing!" Treehugger exclaimed.<br>
<br>
Janeway nodded and smiled.  He den walked closer to Bash and spoke in a quieter tone for only da ogre to hear.  "<i>Arrrgh.  I know ye will be findin' your brother, good ogre.  Arrrgh.  Your heart be bein' full of love and I know he be bein' happy to see you once again.  Arrrgh.  Don't be givin' up hope!  Arrrgh!</i>"<br>
<br>
Da ogre smiled and nodded, but den realized Captain Kirk no could see it.  So Bash stammered a "Tank yous."<br>
<br>
Lilting wlaked up to Wussly and shook da boy's hand.  "Thank you very, very, very, very much for saving us against that mean man who could control space, time, and matter with mere thought!"<br>
<br>
"No problem!  Thanks for helping me figure out that giant, mechanical squid's weakness!"<br>
<br>
"Sure thing!  Thanks for stopping that big cubicle ship full of zombies that wanted to turn us all into zombies too to add to their collective selves!"<br>
<br>
"You're welcome!  Thanks for..."<br>
<br>
"<b>SHUT UP!/ARRRGH!</b>" screamed everyone.<br>
<br>
Da group waved deir goodbyes and was off.  Dey followed da beach to a large, brick archway dat lead to da path dat would take dem through da mountains to Kaladim.<br>
<br>
Taking only two steps on da path, Bash started sniffing da air wit great eagerness.<br>
<br>
"Me smell someting good!!!" da large ogre exclaimed.<br>
<br>
Dey continued walking down da path.  A berry, berry loud rumbling sound was den heard by all, and da source was Bash's tummy.<br>
<br>
"Me smell someting berry good!  Me not know what!  Me starving now!!!"<br>
<br>
Da group still marched on but Bash was almost given over to da lust after da delicious aroma which he could not stop breathing in.<br>
<br>
"Me smell food!  Me smell someting good!  Me smell....!"<br>
<br>
"Dwarves!" Lilting shouted in surprise as many armed dwarves jumped out of da bushes on both sides of da canyon trail.</p>
