<i>Posted by Numbuk on 03-22-2001 08:40 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/Book.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> Chapter 47.</b></p>

<p>"OCH!" shouted all da dwarves surrounding da party in unison.  Dere were at least twenty of da little tings and each of dem held a weapon pointed towards da group.  Some looked like royal guards or some other type of rich warrior, wit deir fine spears and armor shining.  Udders looked like farmers wit deir soiled rags for clothes and pitchforks as weapons.  One ting was clear dough:  all of dem looked battle-weary and none looked too happy to see Bash and his friends.<br>
<br>
"Och, yourself!" said Treehugger pulling out his swords.  "Let us pass, tiny ones!  Our fight is not with you!"<br>
<br>
"Ya best be puttin' yerrr hands up in tha air, all of yas!" growled da head dwarf who had a black beard and a scar dat ran down da left side of his face, permanently closing one eye.<br>
<br>
"I would advise everyone to show no aggression," said Pyra.  "Dwarves are nothing to scoff at when it comes to fighting."<br>
<br>
Bash didn't say a word.  But his stomach growled all da more.<br>
<br>
"Drrrop yer weapons, all of ya!" da dwarf shouted.  "Ah've  been orrrdered ta brrring yas to see the king!  And ain't nuthin gonna stop me!"<br>
<br>
"We will stop you!" said Lilting taking out his tiny, tiny dagger.  "Right guys?!"<br>
<br>
Da band of dwarves just laughed.  Medsa snickered a little bit too.<br>
<br>
"Ya bein' brrrave for a 'scrawny', says I!  But we arrre havin' our orrrders!  Though the few of us could surely be takin' all of yas down, therrre be several more of us hidin' yet!  Ah say again, drrrop yer weapons and come along!"<br>
<br>
Bash snapped out of his hunger trance long enough to realize da situation.  He felt dat he should not fight back.<br>
<br>
"Guys," da ogre said to his friends, "Do as da dorf says.  Me have feeling dat if us fight now, whether we win or lose, our quest will be lost."<br>
<br>
Da group reluctantly listened to da big ogre and dropped deir weapons.  More dwarves jumped out of da bushes.  Dwarves snatched up weapons and udders began tying da party's hands behind deir backs.<br>
<br>
Yessir let out a big sigh.  "This is reminding me of a blind date I had many years ago..."<br>
<br>
"I hope you know what you're doing Bash." said Treehugger uneasily.<br>
<br>
"Me too." said Bash.<br>
<br>
Da dwarves formed a line in front of and behind da group and forced dem to march northward along da path.<br>
<br>
<br>
-----------------<br>
<br>
<br>
Da entrance to da dwarven city of Kaladim was a sight to behold.  It looked even better several weeks before, but  even in a ruined state it was quite impressive.  Da entrance to da city was a grand archway dat led right into da mountain itself.  On top of da archway was a statue of a dwarven warrior, fifty feet tall.  Unfortunately, all dat remained of da statue now was da feet and legs.  Da rest of it was nothing but rubble on da ground surrounding da archway.<br>
<br>
Most of da group couldn't help but stare in awe of da remaining craftsmanship of da statue and cracked archway.  Deir dwarven captors however, muttered curses and udder nasty tings dat Bash no could make out.<br>
<br>
Da dwarves led dem straight into da maw of da dwarven city.<br>
<br>
<br>
-----------------<br>
<br>
<br>
Da inside of da dwarven city was in ruins, but it still looked spectacular.  Though many of da dwarven homes and buildings dat were carved out of da rock were mostly piles of dust, some remained mostly in tact and da group marveled at da craftsmanship.  All throughout da huge city many boulders and stalagtites had  crashed to da ground, crushing many structures, passageways, and dwarves.<br>
<br>
Bruised, bloodied, and obviously battleweary, all da dwarves in da city seemed mostly unphased by da recent disaster.  Hundreds of dwarves were rapidly working on rebuilding deir city.  Many were working on carving out new passages and archways, while udders were mining stones, metals, and jewels for new buildings.<br>
<br>
Bash was glad to see da dwarves busy at rebuilding deir city, but was a little confused as to how dey was doing it.  Da dwarves did not use mining picks or any udder type of tools.  Dey was slamming  deir fists and fingers into da rock walls to mine ore, and occasionally using deir teeth to bite off chunks of rock dey wanted.  Bash's friends also noticed da strange mining technique of da dwarves.<br>
<br>
"Did you guys lose all your mining picks in the earthquake?" asked Treehugger to one of da dwarves dat lead da party.<br>
<br>
"Mining what?" grunted da dirty dwarf.<br>
<br>
"Picks!  You know, a tool with a double metal blade with a wooden handle that you can use to help you mine better!  Orcs drop them all the time!"<br>
<br>
"No idea what yer talkin' about, boy!  Besides, who needs these 'prick thingies' when we have our teeth?!"<br>
<br>
A bunch of da dwarves smiled at Treehugger, and da ranger saw dat many of da little fellows were missing many teeth and udders and chipped and worn-down-to-da-nub teeth.  Looking around, da half-elf noticed dat dis dental occurance was not uncommon among da hundreds of dwarves.<br>
<br>
Da group arrived at what used to be a grand hall dat lead to a massive, beautiful door.  Dis was obviously da  entrance to someone important.  Four dwarves pushed back each door.<br>
<br>
"In ya go, surface dwellers!  Go to the king, and be judged!" shouted da head dwarf.<br>
<br>
<br>
-------------<br>
<br>
<br>
Da group stood in an elaborate throne room.  Guards in polished armor lined da red carpet leading up to da fattest, ugliest, and smelliest dwarf of all.  His beard was probably white, but it was brown from all da grease and chicken bits dat had fallen into it.  He wore a long purple robe and a gold crown.  Next to him sat a slim dwarven female, who had a brown beard almost as long as da king's, but was much cleaner.  She was also dressed in a purple robe.<br>
<br>
Bash's stomach started rumbling at da sight of da fat king dwarf.  Da smell from da chicken grease in his beard no helped much either.<br>
<br>
Da dwarves dat captured da party all bowed down, and da head dwarf began speaking.  "King Kazon and Queen Nozak, these are tha people whom yer Royal Seer told ya about, and the ones whom ya ordered me ta get!"<br>
<br>
King Kazon scowled at da party of Bash.  "You!  You big meanheads!  You did this to us!"   Da king started hopping up in down in rage.  "You you you you you!"<br>
<br>
Medsa began to say someting, but was silenced by a guard.<br>
<br>
Da king began shouting some more.  "Where is my seer?!  And where is my food?!"<br>
<br>
Da queen began to calmly speak to her husband.  "Dear, you just ate.  Shouldn't you take your doctor's advice and not eat as often, especially greasy foods?"<br>
<br>
"Shut up you dum-dum woman!  You're just a queen!  I'm the king!  I make the law!  I make the medical advice!  I order my body to stay healthy!"<br>
<br>
"But dear, you eat so much chicken that your blood is probably nothing more than a chicken broth..."<br>
<br>
Bash's stomach began to moan in agony.<br>
<br>
Da queen continued, "...and I don't want to see you have a heart attack."<br>
<br>
"Shut up!  Ah, here comes the seer!"<br>
<br>
An old, old dwarf entered da room.  His white beard dangled to da ground from his wrinkly face.  He inspected da group closely and den went to da king.<br>
<br>
"Yes, these are the ones whom I spoke of.  They are somehow tied to the black knight that came here, though I don't believe they sent it."<br>
<br>
"Shut up!  What do you know?  I bet they sent it!"  Da king began hopping up and down wit fists clenched, screaming all da while.  "I order them to be executed at dawn!  Lock them in the prison!"<br>
<br>
Lilting and Pyra winked at each udder upon hearing dat.<br>
<br>
Da seer looked at da group.  "My lord, they have a druid and a wizard amongst them.  Both are capable of teleportation."<br>
<br>
"Shut up!" shouted the king.  "I know that!  Throw them in the "Magically Sealed" prison then!"<br>
<br>
"D'oh!" whispered Pyra and Lilting inaudibly.</p>
